B040C008V001	40	8	1	When he was come down from the mountain, great multitudes followed him.
B040C008V002	40	8	2	And, behold, there came a leper and worshipped him, saying, Lord, if you will, you can make me clean.
B040C008V003	40	8	3	And Jesus put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, 
B040C008V004	40	8	4	And Jesus says unto him, 
B040C008V005	40	8	5	And when Jesus was entered into Capernaum, there came unto him a centurion, beseeching him,
B040C008V006	40	8	6	And saying, Lord, my servant lies at home sick of the palsy, grievously tormented.
B040C008V007	40	8	7	And Jesus says unto him, 
B040C008V008	40	8	8	The centurion answered and said, Lord, I am not worthy that you should come under my roof: but speak the word only, and my servant shall be healed.
B040C008V009	40	8	9	For I am a man of authority, having soldiers under me: and I say to this man, Go, and he goes; and to another, Come, and he comes; and to my servant, Do this, and he does it.
B040C008V010	40	8	10	When Jesus heard it, he marvelled, and said to them that followed, 
B040C008V011	40	8	11	
        
B040C008V012	40	8	12	
        
B040C008V013	40	8	13	And Jesus said unto the centurion, 
B040C008V014	40	8	14	And when Jesus was come into Peter's house, he saw his wife's mother laid down, and burning with fever.
B040C008V015	40	8	15	And he touched her hand, and the fever left her: and she arose, and ministered unto them.
B040C008V016	40	8	16	When the evening was come, they brought unto him many that were possessed with devils: and he cast out the spirits with his word, and healed all that were sick:
B040C008V017	40	8	17	That it might be fulfilled which was spoken by Isaiah the prophet, saying, He took our infirmities, and bore our sicknesses.
B040C008V018	40	8	18	Now when Jesus saw great multitudes about him, he gave commandment to depart unto the other side.
B040C008V019	40	8	19	And a certain scribe came, and said unto him, Master, I will follow you to wherever you go.
B040C008V020	40	8	20	And Jesus says unto him, 
B040C008V021	40	8	21	And another of his disciples said unto him, Lord, permit me first to go and bury my father.
B040C008V022	40	8	22	But Jesus said unto him, 
B040C008V023	40	8	23	And when he was entered into a boat, his disciples followed him.
B040C008V024	40	8	24	And, behold, there arose a great tempest in the sea, insomuch that the boat was covered with the waves: but he was asleep.
B040C008V025	40	8	25	And his disciples came to him, and awoke him, saying, Lord, save us: we perish.
B040C008V026	40	8	26	And he says unto them, 
B040C008V027	40	8	27	But the men marvelled, saying, What manner of man is this, that even the winds and the sea obey him!
B040C008V028	40	8	28	And when he was come to the other side into the country of the Gergesenes, there met him two possessed with devils, coming out of the tombs, exceedingly fierce, so that no man might pass by that way.
B040C008V029	40	8	29	And, behold, they cried out, saying, What have we to do with you, Jesus, you Son of God? are you come here to torment us before the time?
B040C008V030	40	8	30	And there was a good way off from them a herd of many swine feeding.
B040C008V031	40	8	31	So the devils besought him, saying, If you cast us out, permit us to go away into the herd of swine.
B040C008V032	40	8	32	And he said unto them, Go. And when they had come out, they went into the herd of swine: and, behold, the whole herd of swine ran violently down a steep place into the sea, and perished in the waters.
B040C008V033	40	8	33	And they that kept them fled, and went their ways into the city, and told everything, and what was befallen to those possessed of the devils.
B040C008V034	40	8	34	And, behold, the whole city came out to meet Jesus: and when they saw him, they asked him to depart out of their borders.
