B041C014V037	41	14	37	And he comes, and finds them sleeping, and says unto Peter, 
B041C014V038	41	14	38	
        
B041C014V039	41	14	39	And again he went away, and prayed, and spoke the same words.
B041C014V040	41	14	40	And when he returned, he found them asleep again, (for their eyes were heavy,) neither did they know what to answer him.
B041C014V041	41	14	41	And he comes the third time, and says unto them, 
B041C014V042	41	14	42	
        
B041C014V043	41	14	43	And immediately, while he yet spoke, comes Judas, one of the twelve, and with him a great multitude with swords and staves, from the chief priests and the scribes and the elders.
B041C014V044	41	14	44	And he that betrayed him had given them a token, saying, Whomsoever I shall kiss, that same is he; take him, and lead him away safely.
B041C014V045	41	14	45	And as soon as he was come, he goes immediately to him, and says, Master, master; and kissed him.
B041C014V046	41	14	46	And they laid their hands on him, and took him.
B041C014V047	41	14	47	And one of them that stood by drew a sword, and smote a servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.
B041C014V048	41	14	48	And Jesus answered and said unto them, 
B041C014V049	41	14	49	
        
B041C014V050	41	14	50	And they all forsook him, and fled.
B041C014V051	41	14	51	And there followed him a certain young man, having a linen cloth cast about his naked body; and the young men laid hold on him:
B041C014V052	41	14	52	And he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked.
B041C014V053	41	14	53	And they led Jesus away to the high priest: and with him were assembled all the chief priests and the elders and the scribes.
B041C014V054	41	14	54	And Peter followed him afar off, even into the palace of the high priest: and he sat with the servants, and warmed himself at the fire.
B041C014V055	41	14	55	And the chief priests and all the council sought for witness against Jesus to put him to death; and found none.
B041C014V056	41	14	56	For many bare false witness against him, but their witness agreed not together.
B041C014V057	41	14	57	And there arose certain, and bare false witness against him, saying,
B041C014V058	41	14	58	We heard him say, I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and within three days I will build another made without hands.
B041C014V059	41	14	59	But neither so did their witness agree together.
B041C014V060	41	14	60	And the high priest stood up in the midst, and asked Jesus, saying, Answer you nothing? what is it which these witness against you?
B041C014V061	41	14	61	But he held his peace, and answered nothing. Again the high priest asked him, and said unto him, Are you the Christ, the Son of the Blessed?
B041C014V062	41	14	62	And Jesus said, 
B041C014V063	41	14	63	Then the high priest tore his clothes, and says, What need we any further witnesses?
B041C014V064	41	14	64	You have heard the blasphemy: what think you? And they all condemned him to be guilty of death.
B041C014V065	41	14	65	And some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to buffet him, and to say unto him, Prophesy: and the servants did strike him with the palms of their hands.
B041C014V066	41	14	66	And as Peter was beneath in the palace, there comes one of the maids of the high priest:
B041C014V067	41	14	67	And when she saw Peter warming himself, she looked upon him, and said, And you also were with Jesus of Nazareth.
B041C014V068	41	14	68	But he denied, saying, I do not know, neither understand I what you say. And he went out into the porch; and the cock crowed.
B041C014V069	41	14	69	And a maid saw him again, and began to say to them that stood by, This is one of them.
B041C014V070	41	14	70	And he denied it again. And a little after, they that stood by said again to Peter, Surely you are one of them: for you are a Galilaean, and your speech agrees to that.
B041C014V071	41	14	71	But he began to curse and to swear, saying, I do not know this man of whom you speak.
B041C014V072	41	14	72	And the second time the cock crowed. And Peter called to mind the word that Jesus said unto him, 
B041C015V001	41	15	1	And immediately in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried him away, and delivered him to Pilate.
B041C015V002	41	15	2	And Pilate asked him, Are you the King of the Jews? And he answering said unto them, 
B041C015V003	41	15	3	And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing.
B041C015V004	41	15	4	And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answer you nothing? behold how many things they witness against you.
B041C015V005	41	15	5	But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marvelled.
B041C015V006	41	15	6	Now at that feast he released unto them one prisoner, whoever they desired.
B041C015V007	41	15	7	And there was one named Barabbas, which lay bound with them that had made insurrection with him, who had committed murder in the insurrection.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	And the multitude crying aloud began to desire him to do as he had always done unto them.
B041C015V009	41	15	9	But Pilate answered them, saying, Will you that I release unto you the King of the Jews?
B041C015V010	41	15	10	For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him because of.
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests moved the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will you then that I shall do unto him whom you call the King of the Jews?
B041C015V013	41	15	13	And they cried out again, Crucify him.
B041C015V014	41	15	14	Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil has he done? And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.
B041C015V015	41	15	15	And so Pilate, willing to content the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had whipped him, to be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they call together the whole band.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his head,
B041C015V018	41	15	18	And began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!
B041C015V019	41	15	19	And they smote him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing their knees worshipped him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	And they compel one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming out of the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	And they bring him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull.
B041C015V023	41	15	23	And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received it not.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots upon them, what every man should take.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And the superscription of his accusation was written over, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B041C015V027	41	15	27	And with him they crucify two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.
B041C015V028	41	15	28	And the scripture was fulfilled, which says, And he was numbered with the transgressors.
B041C015V029	41	15	29	And they that passed by railed on him, wagging their heads, and saying, Ah, you that destroys the temple, and builds it in three days,
B041C015V030	41	15	30	Save yourself, and come down from the cross.
B041C015V031	41	15	31	Likewise also the chief priests mocking said among themselves with the scribes, He saved others; himself he cannot save.
B041C015V032	41	15	32	Let Christ the King of Israel descend now from the cross, that we may see and believe. And they that were crucified with him reviled him.
B041C015V033	41	15	33	And when the sixth hour was come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth hour.
B041C015V034	41	15	34	And at the ninth hour Jesus cried with a loud voice, saying, 
B041C015V035	41	15	35	And some of them that stood by, when they heard it, said, Behold, he calls Elijah.
B041C015V036	41	15	36	And one ran and filled a sponge full of vinegar, and put it on a reed, and gave him to drink, saying, Let him alone; let us see whether Elijah will come to take him down.
B041C015V037	41	15	37	And Jesus cried with a loud voice, and gave up the ghost.
B041C015V038	41	15	38	And the veil of the temple was torn in two from the top to the bottom.
B041C015V039	41	15	39	And when the centurion, which stood over against him, saw that he so cried out, and gave up the ghost, he said, Truly this man was the Son of God.
B041C015V040	41	15	40	There were also women looking on afar off: among whom was Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James the less and of Joses, and Salome;
B041C015V041	41	15	41	(Who also, when he was in Galilee, followed him, and ministered unto him;) and many other women which came up with him unto Jerusalem.
B041C015V042	41	15	42	And now when the even was come, because it was the preparation, that is, the day before the sabbath,
B041C015V043	41	15	43	Joseph of Arimathaea, an honorable counselor, which also waited for the kingdom of God, came, and went in boldly unto Pilate, and requested the body of Jesus.
B041C015V044	41	15	44	And Pilate wondered if he were already dead: and calling unto him the centurion, he asked him whether he had been any while dead.
B041C015V045	41	15	45	And when he knew it of the centurion, he gave the body to Joseph.
B041C015V046	41	15	46	And he bought fine linen, and took him down, and wrapped him in the linen, and laid him in a sepulcher which was hewn out of a rock, and rolled a stone unto the door of the sepulcher.
B041C015V047	41	15	47	And Mary Magdalene and Mary the mother of Joses beheld where he was laid.
B041C016V001	41	16	1	And when the sabbath was past, Mary Magdalene, and Mary the mother of James, and Salome, had bought sweet spices, that they might come and anoint him.
B041C016V002	41	16	2	And very early in the morning the first day of the week, they came unto the sepulcher at the rising of the sun.
B041C016V003	41	16	3	And they said among themselves, Who shall roll us away the stone from the door of the sepulcher?
B041C016V004	41	16	4	And when they looked, they saw that the stone was rolled away: for it was very great.
B041C016V005	41	16	5	And entering into the sepulcher, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, clothed in a long white garment; and they were frightened.
B041C016V006	41	16	6	And he says unto them, Be not frightened: You seek Jesus of Nazareth, which was crucified: he is risen; he is not here: behold the place where they laid him.
B041C016V007	41	16	7	But go your way, tell his disciples and Peter that he goes before you into Galilee: there shall you see him, as he said unto you.
B041C016V008	41	16	8	And they went out quickly, and fled from the sepulcher; for they trembled and were amazed: neither said they any thing to any man; for they were afraid.
B041C016V009	41	16	9	Now when Jesus was risen early the first day of the week, he appeared first to Mary Magdalene, out of whom he had cast seven devils.
B041C016V010	41	16	10	And she went and told them that had been with him, as they mourned and wept.
B041C016V011	41	16	11	And they, when they had heard that he was alive, and had been seen of her, believed not.
B041C016V012	41	16	12	After that he appeared in another form unto two of them, as they walked, and went into the country.
B041C016V013	41	16	13	And they went and told it unto the others: neither believed they them.
B041C016V014	41	16	14	Afterward he appeared unto the eleven as they sat at food, and upbraided them with their unbelief and hardness of heart, because they believed not those who had seen him after he was risen.
B041C016V015	41	16	15	And he said unto them, 
B041C016V016	41	16	16	
        
B041C016V017	41	16	17	
        
B041C016V018	41	16	18	
        
B041C016V019	41	16	19	So then after the Lord had spoken unto them, he was received up into heaven, and sat on the right hand of God.
B041C016V020	41	16	20	And they went forth, and preached everywhere, the Lord working with them, and confirming the word with signs following. Amen.
B042C001V001	42	1	1	Since many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of those things which are most surely believed among us,
B042C001V002	42	1	2	Just as they delivered them unto us, which from the beginning were eyewitnesses, and ministers of the word;
B042C001V003	42	1	3	It seemed good to me also, having had perfect understanding of all things from the very first, to write unto you in order, most excellent Theophilus,
B042C001V004	42	1	4	That you might know the certainty of those things, in which you have been instructed.
B042C001V005	42	1	5	There was in the days of Herod, the king of Judaea, a certain priest named Zacharias, of the course of Abia: and his wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elisabeth.
B042C001V006	42	1	6	And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of the Lord blameless.
B042C001V007	42	1	7	And they had no child, because Elisabeth was barren, and they both were now well advanced in years.
B042C001V008	42	1	8	And it came to pass, that while he executed the priest's office before God in the order of his course,
B042C001V009	42	1	9	According to the custom of the priest's office, his lot was to burn incense when he went into the temple of the Lord.
B042C001V010	42	1	10	And the whole multitude of the people were praying outside at the time of incense.
B042C001V011	42	1	11	And there appeared unto him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar of incense.
B042C001V012	42	1	12	And when Zacharias saw him, he was troubled, and fear fell upon him.
B042C001V013	42	1	13	But the angel said unto him, Fear not, Zacharias: for your prayer is heard; and your wife Elisabeth shall bear you a son, and you shall call his name John.
B042C001V014	42	1	14	And you shall have joy and gladness; and many shall rejoice at his birth.
B042C001V015	42	1	15	For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong drink; and he shall be filled with the Holy Ghost, even from his mother's womb.
B042C001V016	42	1	16	And many of the children of Israel shall he turn to the Lord their God.
B042C001V017	42	1	17	And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elijah, to turn the hearts of the fathers to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just; to make ready a people prepared for the Lord.
B042C001V018	42	1	18	And Zacharias said unto the angel, How shall I know this? for I am an old man, and my wife well advanced in years.
B042C001V019	42	1	19	And the angel answering said unto him, I am Gabriel, that stand in the presence of God; and am sent to speak unto you, and to show you these glad tidings.
B042C001V020	42	1	20	And, behold, you shall be dumb, and not able to speak, until the day that these things shall be performed, because you believe not my words, which shall be fulfilled in their appropriate time.
B042C001V021	42	1	21	And the people waited for Zacharias, and wondered why he tarried so long in the temple.
B042C001V022	42	1	22	And when he came out, he could not speak unto them: and they perceived that he had seen a vision in the temple: for he beckoned unto them, and remained speechless.
B042C001V023	42	1	23	And it came to pass, that, as soon as the days of his ministration were accomplished, he departed to his own house.
B042C001V024	42	1	24	And after those days his wife Elisabeth conceived, and hid herself five months, saying,
B042C001V025	42	1	25	Thus has the Lord dealt with me in the days in which he looked on me, to take away my reproach among men.
B042C001V026	42	1	26	And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God unto a city of Galilee, named Nazareth,
B042C001V027	42	1	27	To a virgin espoused to a man whose name was Joseph, of the house of David; and the virgin's name was Mary.
B042C001V028	42	1	28	And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail, you that are highly favored, the Lord is with you: blessed are you among women.
B042C001V029	42	1	29	And when she saw him, she was troubled at his saying, and cast in her mind what manner of salutation this should be.
B042C001V030	42	1	30	And the angel said unto her, Fear not, Mary: for you have found favor with God.
B042C001V031	42	1	31	And, behold, you shall conceive in your womb, and bring forth a son, and shall call his name JESUS.
B042C001V032	42	1	32	He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest: and the Lord God shall give unto him the throne of his father David:
B042C001V033	42	1	33	And he shall reign over the house of Jacob forever; and of his kingdom there shall be no end.
B042C001V034	42	1	34	Then said Mary unto the angel, How shall this be, seeing I know not a man?
B042C001V035	42	1	35	And the angel answered and said unto her, The Holy Ghost shall come upon you, and the power of the Highest shall overshadow you: therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of you shall be called the Son of God.
B042C001V036	42	1	36	And, behold, your cousin Elisabeth, she has also conceived a son in her old age: and this is the sixth month with her, who was called barren.
B042C001V037	42	1	37	For with God nothing shall be impossible.
B042C001V038	42	1	38	And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord; be it unto me according to your word. And the angel departed from her.
B042C001V039	42	1	39	And Mary arose in those days, and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of Juda;
B042C001V040	42	1	40	And entered into the house of Zacharias, and saluted Elisabeth.
B042C001V041	42	1	41	And it came to pass, that, when Elisabeth heard the salutation of Mary, the babe leaped in her womb; and Elisabeth was filled with the Holy Ghost:
B042C001V042	42	1	42	And she spoke out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed are you among women, and blessed is the fruit of your womb.
B042C001V043	42	1	43	And why is this to me, that the mother of my Lord should come to me?
B042C001V044	42	1	44	For, lo, as soon as the voice of your salutation sounded in my ears, the babe leaped in my womb for joy.
B042C001V045	42	1	45	And blessed is she that believed: for there shall be a performance of those things which were told her from the Lord.
B042C001V046	42	1	46	And Mary said, My soul does magnify the Lord,
B042C001V047	42	1	47	And my spirit has rejoiced in God my Saviour.
B042C001V048	42	1	48	For he has regarded the low estate of his handmaiden: for, behold, from henceforth all generations shall call me blessed.
B042C001V049	42	1	49	For he that is mighty has done to me great things; and holy is his name.
B042C001V050	42	1	50	And his mercy is on them that fear him from generation to generation.
B042C001V051	42	1	51	He has showed strength with his arm; he has scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.
B042C001V052	42	1	52	He has put down the mighty from their seats, and exalted them of low degree.
B042C001V053	42	1	53	He has filled the hungry with good things; and the rich he has sent empty away.
B042C001V054	42	1	54	He has helped his servant Israel, in remembrance of his mercy;
B042C001V055	42	1	55	As he spoke to our fathers, to Abraham, and to his seed forever.
B042C001V056	42	1	56	And Mary abode with her about three months, and returned to her own house.
B042C001V057	42	1	57	Now Elisabeth's full time came that she should be delivered; and she brought forth a son.
B042C001V058	42	1	58	And her neighbors and her cousins heard how the Lord had showed great mercy upon her; and they rejoiced with her.
B042C001V059	42	1	59	And it came to pass, that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child; and they called him Zacharias, after the name of his father.
B042C001V060	42	1	60	And his mother answered and said, Not so; but he shall be called John.
B042C001V061	42	1	61	And they said unto her, There is none of your kindred that is called by this name.
B042C001V062	42	1	62	And they made signs to his father, how he would have him called.
B042C001V063	42	1	63	And he asked for a writing table, and wrote, saying, His name is John. And they marvelled all.
B042C001V064	42	1	64	And his mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue loosed, and he spoke, and praised God.
B042C001V065	42	1	65	And fear came on all that dwelled round about them: and all these sayings were reported abroad throughout all the hill country of Judaea.
B042C001V066	42	1	66	And all they that heard them laid them up in their hearts, saying, What manner of child shall this be! And the hand of the Lord was with him.
B042C001V067	42	1	67	And his father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Ghost, and prophesied, saying,
B042C001V068	42	1	68	Blessed be the Lord God of Israel; for he has visited and redeemed his people,
B042C001V069	42	1	69	And has raised up a horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David;
B042C001V070	42	1	70	As he spoke by the mouth of his holy prophets, which have been since the world began:
B042C001V071	42	1	71	That we should be saved from our enemies, and from the hand of all that hate us;
B042C001V072	42	1	72	To perform the mercy promised to our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant;
B042C001V073	42	1	73	The oath which he helped to our father Abraham,
B042C001V074	42	1	74	That he would grant unto us, that we being delivered out of the hand of our enemies might serve him without fear,
B042C001V075	42	1	75	In holiness and righteousness before him, all the days of our life.
B042C001V076	42	1	76	And you, child, shall be called the prophet of the Highest: for you shall go before the face of the Lord to prepare his ways;
B042C001V077	42	1	77	To give knowledge of salvation unto his people by the remission of their sins,
B042C001V078	42	1	78	Through the tender mercy of our God; whereby the dayspring from on high has visited us,
B042C001V079	42	1	79	To give light to them that sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace.
B042C001V080	42	1	80	And the child grew, and grew strong in spirit, and was in the deserted places till the day of his appearance unto Israel.
B042C002V001	42	2	1	And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus that all the world should be registered.
B042C002V002	42	2	2	(And this registration was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.)
B042C002V003	42	2	3	And all went to be registered, every one into his own city.
B042C002V004	42	2	4	And Joseph also went up from Galilee, out of the city of Nazareth, into Judaea, unto the city of David, which is called Bethlehem; (because he was of the house and lineage of David:)
B042C002V005	42	2	5	To be registered with Mary his espoused wife, being great with child.
B042C002V006	42	2	6	And so it was, that, while they were there, the days were accomplished that she should be delivered.
B042C002V007	42	2	7	And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid him in a manger; because there was no room for them in the inn.
B042C002V008	42	2	8	And there were in the same country shepherds abiding in the field, keeping watch over their flock by night.
B042C002V009	42	2	9	And, lo, the angel of the Lord came upon them, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them: and they were intensely afraid.
B042C002V010	42	2	10	And the angel said unto them, Fear not: for, behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy, which shall be to all people.
B042C002V011	42	2	11	For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Saviour, which is Christ the Lord.
B042C002V012	42	2	12	And this shall be a sign unto you; You shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes, lying in a manger.
B042C002V013	42	2	13	And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host praising God, and saying,
B042C002V014	42	2	14	Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, good will toward men.
B042C002V015	42	2	15	And it came to pass, as the angels were gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds said one to another, Let us now go even unto Bethlehem, and see this thing which is come to pass, which the Lord has made known unto us.
B042C002V016	42	2	16	And they came with haste, and found Mary, and Joseph, and the babe lying in a manger.
B042C002V017	42	2	17	And when they had seen it, they made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning this child.
B042C002V018	42	2	18	And all they that heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.
B042C002V019	42	2	19	But Mary kept all these things, and pondered them in her heart.
B042C002V020	42	2	20	And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they had heard and seen, as it was told unto them.
B042C002V021	42	2	21	And when eight days were accomplished for the circumcising of the child, his name was called JESUS, which was so named of the angel before he was conceived in the womb.
B042C002V022	42	2	22	And when the days of her purification according to the law of Moses were accomplished, they brought him to Jerusalem, to present him to the Lord;
B042C002V023	42	2	23	(As it is written in the law of the LORD, Every male that opens the womb shall be called holy to the Lord;)
B042C002V024	42	2	24	And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, A pair of turtledoves, or two young pigeons.
