B043C001V001	43	1	1	In the beginning was the Word, and the Word was with God, and the Word was God.
B043C001V002	43	1	2	The same was in the beginning with God.
B043C001V003	43	1	3	All things were made by him; and outside him was not any thing made that was made.
B043C001V004	43	1	4	In him was life; and the life was the light of men.
B043C001V005	43	1	5	And the light shines in darkness; and the darkness comprehended it not.
B043C001V006	43	1	6	There was a man sent from God, whose name was John.
B043C001V007	43	1	7	The same came for a witness, to bear witness of the Light, that all men through him might believe.
B043C001V008	43	1	8	He was not that Light, but was sent to bear witness of that Light.
B043C001V009	43	1	9	That was the true Light, which lights every man that comes into the world.
B043C001V010	43	1	10	He was in the world, and the world was made by him, and the world knew him not.
B043C001V011	43	1	11	He came unto his own, and his own received him not.
B043C001V012	43	1	12	But as many as received him, to them gave he power to become the sons of God, even to them that believe on his name:
B043C001V013	43	1	13	Which were born, not of blood, nor of the will of the flesh, nor of the will of man, but of God.
B043C001V014	43	1	14	And the Word was made flesh, and dwelled among us, (and we beheld his glory, the glory as of the only begotten of the Father,) full of grace and truth.
B043C001V015	43	1	15	John bore witness of him, and cried, saying, This was he of whom I spoke, He that comes after me is preferred before me: for he was before me.
B043C001V016	43	1	16	And of his fullness have all we received, and grace for grace.
B043C001V017	43	1	17	For the law was given by Moses, but grace and truth came by Jesus Christ.
B043C001V018	43	1	18	No man has seen God at any time, the only begotten Son, which is in the bosom of the Father, he has declared him.
B043C001V019	43	1	19	And this is the record of John, when the Jews sent priests and Levites from Jerusalem to ask him, Who are you?
B043C001V020	43	1	20	And he confessed, and denied not; but confessed, I am not the Christ.
B043C001V021	43	1	21	And they asked him, What then? Are you Elijah? And he says, I am not. Are you that prophet? And he answered, No.
B043C001V022	43	1	22	Then said they unto him, Who are you? that we may give an answer to them that sent us. What say you of yourself?
B043C001V023	43	1	23	He said, I am the voice of one crying in the wilderness, Make straight the way of the Lord, as said the prophet Isaiah.
B043C001V024	43	1	24	And they which were sent were of the Pharisees.
B043C001V025	43	1	25	And they asked him, and said unto him, Why do you baptize then, if you be not that Christ, nor Elijah, neither that prophet?
B043C001V026	43	1	26	John answered them, saying, I baptize with water: but there stands one among you, whom you know not;
B043C001V027	43	1	27	He it is, who coming after me is preferred before me, whose shoe's latchet I am not worthy to unloose.
B043C001V028	43	1	28	These things were done in Bethabara beyond the Jordan, where John was baptizing.
B043C001V029	43	1	29	The next day John sees Jesus coming unto him, and says, Behold the Lamb of God, which takes away the sin of the world.
B043C001V030	43	1	30	This is he of whom I said, After me comes a man which is preferred before me: for he was before me.
B043C001V031	43	1	31	And I knew him not: but that he should be made manifest to Israel, therefore am I come baptizing with water.
B043C001V032	43	1	32	And John bore record, saying, I saw the Spirit descending from heaven like a dove, and it abode upon him.
B043C001V033	43	1	33	And I knew him not: but he that sent me to baptize with water, the same said unto me, Upon whom you shall see the Spirit descending, and remaining on him, the same is he which baptizes with the Holy Ghost.
B043C001V034	43	1	34	And I saw, and bore record that this is the Son of God.
