B044C007V020	44	7	20	In which time Moses was born, and was exceedingly fair, and nourished up in his father's house three months:
B044C007V021	44	7	21	And when he was cast out, Pharaoh's daughter took him up, and nourished him for her own son.
B044C007V022	44	7	22	And Moses was learned in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was mighty in words and in deeds.
B044C007V023	44	7	23	And when he was full forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brothers the children of Israel.
B044C007V024	44	7	24	And seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him that was oppressed, and smote the Egyptian:
B044C007V025	44	7	25	For he supposed his brothers would have understood that God by his hand would deliver them: but they understood not.
B044C007V026	44	7	26	And the next day he showed himself unto them as they strove, and would have set them at one again, saying, Sirs, you are brothers; why do you wrong one to another?
B044C007V027	44	7	27	But he that did his neighbor wrong thrust him away, saying, Who made you a ruler and a judge over us?
B044C007V028	44	7	28	Do you want kill me, as you did the Egyptian yesterday?
B044C007V029	44	7	29	Then fled Moses at this saying, and was a stranger in the land of Madian, where he begat two sons.
B044C007V030	44	7	30	And when forty years were expired, there appeared to him in the wilderness of mount Sina an angel of the Lord in a flame of fire in a bush.
B044C007V031	44	7	31	When Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight: and as he drew near to behold it, the voice of the LORD came unto him,
B044C007V032	44	7	32	Saying, I am the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob. Then Moses trembled, and dared not behold.
B044C007V033	44	7	33	Then said the Lord to him, Put off your shoes from your feet: for the place where you stand is holy ground.
B044C007V034	44	7	34	I have seen, I have seen the affliction of my people which is in Egypt, and I have heard their groaning, and am come down to deliver them. And now come, I will send you into Egypt.
