B044C008V019	44	8	19	Saying, Give me also this power, that on whomsoever I lay hands, he may receive the Holy Ghost.
B044C008V020	44	8	20	But Peter said unto him, Your money perish with you, because you have thought that the gift of God may be purchased with money.
B044C008V021	44	8	21	You have neither part nor lot in this matter: for your heart is not right in the sight of God.
B044C008V022	44	8	22	Repent therefore of this your wickedness, and pray God, if perhaps the thought of your heart may be forgiven you.
B044C008V023	44	8	23	For I perceive that you are in the gall of bitterness, and in the bond of iniquity.
B044C008V024	44	8	24	Then answered Simon, and said, Pray you to the LORD for me, that none of these things which you have spoken come upon me.
B044C008V025	44	8	25	And they, when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem, and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.
B044C008V026	44	8	26	And the angel of the Lord spoke unto Philip, saying, Arise, and go toward the south unto the way that goes down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is deserted.
B044C008V027	44	8	27	And he arose and went: and, behold, a man of Ethiopia, an eunuch of great authority under Candace queen of the Ethiopians, who had the charge of all her treasure, and had come to Jerusalem for to worship,
B044C008V028	44	8	28	Was returning, and sitting in his chariot read Isaiah the prophet.
