B044C010V022	44	10	22	And they said, Cornelius the centurion, a just man, and one that fears God, and of good report among all the nation of the Jews, was warned from God by a holy angel to send for you into his house, and to hear words of you.
B044C010V023	44	10	23	Then called he them in, and lodged them. And on the next day Peter went away with them, and certain brothers from Joppa accompanied him.
B044C010V024	44	10	24	And the next day after they entered into Caesarea. And Cornelius waited for them, and he had called together his kinsmen and near friends.
B044C010V025	44	10	25	And as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet, and worshipped him.
B044C010V026	44	10	26	But Peter took him up, saying, Stand up; I myself also am a man.
B044C010V027	44	10	27	And as he talked with him, he went in, and found many that were come together.
B044C010V028	44	10	28	And he said unto them, You know that it is an unlawful thing for a man that is a Jew to keep company, or come unto one of another nation; but God has showed me that I should not call any man common or unclean.
B044C010V029	44	10	29	Therefore came I unto you without opposing, as soon as I was sent for: I ask therefore for what intent you have sent for me?
B044C010V030	44	10	30	And Cornelius said, Four days ago I was fasting until this hour; and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house, and, behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,
B044C010V031	44	10	31	And said, Cornelius, your prayer is heard, and your alms are had in remembrance in the sight of God.
B044C010V032	44	10	32	Send therefore to Joppa, and call to here Simon, whose surname is Peter; he is lodged in the house of one Simon a tanner by the sea side: who, when he comes, shall speak unto you.
B044C010V033	44	10	33	Immediately therefore I sent to you; and you have well done that you are come. Now therefore are we all here present before God, to hear all things that are commanded you of God.
B044C010V034	44	10	34	Then Peter opened his mouth, and said, Of a truth I perceive that God is no respecter of persons:
B044C010V035	44	10	35	But in every nation he that fears him, and works righteousness, is accepted with him.
B044C010V036	44	10	36	The word which God sent unto the children of Israel, preaching peace by Jesus Christ: (he is Lord of all:)
B044C010V037	44	10	37	That word, I say, you know, which was spoken out throughout all Judaea, and began from Galilee, after the baptism which John preached;
B044C010V038	44	10	38	How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Ghost and with power: who went about doing good, and healing all that were oppressed of the devil; for God was with him.
B044C010V039	44	10	39	And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews, and in Jerusalem; whom they slew and hanged on a tree:
B044C010V040	44	10	40	Him God raised up the third day, and showed him openly;
B044C010V041	44	10	41	Not to all the people, but unto witnesses chosen before God, even to us, who did eat and drink with him after he rose from the dead.
B044C010V042	44	10	42	And he commanded us to preach unto the people, and to testify that it is he which was ordained of God to be the Judge of quick and dead.
B044C010V043	44	10	43	To him give all the prophets witness, that through his name whosoever believes in him shall receive remission of sins.
B044C010V044	44	10	44	While Peter yet spoke these words, the Holy Ghost fell on all those who heard the word.
B044C010V045	44	10	45	And they of the circumcision which believed were astonished, as many as came with Peter, because on the Gentiles also was poured out the gift of the Holy Ghost.
B044C010V046	44	10	46	For they heard them speak with tongues, and magnify God. Then answered Peter,
B044C010V047	44	10	47	Can any man forbid water, that these should not be baptized, which have received the Holy Ghost as well as we?
B044C010V048	44	10	48	And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord. Then prayed they him to tarry certain days.
B044C011V001	44	11	1	And the apostles and brothers that were in Judaea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God.
B044C011V002	44	11	2	And when Peter was come up to Jerusalem, they that were of the circumcision contended with him,
B044C011V003	44	11	3	Saying, You went in to men uncircumcised, and did eat with them.
B044C011V004	44	11	4	But Peter rehearsed the matter from the beginning, and expounded it by order unto them, saying,
B044C011V005	44	11	5	I was in the city of Joppa praying: and in a trance I saw a vision, A certain vessel descend, as it had been a great sheet, let down from heaven by four corners; and it came even to me:
B044C011V006	44	11	6	Upon the which when I had fastened my eyes, I considered, and saw fourfooted beasts of the earth, and wild beasts, and creeping things, and fowls of the air.
B044C011V007	44	11	7	And I heard a voice saying unto me, 
B044C011V008	44	11	8	But I said, Not so, Lord: for nothing common or unclean has at any time entered into my mouth.
B044C011V009	44	11	9	But the voice answered me again from heaven, 
B044C011V010	44	11	10	And this was done three times: and all were drawn up again into heaven.
B044C011V011	44	11	11	And, behold, immediately there were three men already come unto the house where I was, sent from Caesarea unto me.
B044C011V012	44	11	12	And the Spirit bade me go with them, nothing doubting. Moreover these six brothers accompanied me, and we entered into the man's house:
B044C011V013	44	11	13	And he showed us how he had seen an angel in his house, which stood and said unto him, Send men to Joppa, and call for Simon, whose surname is Peter;
B044C011V014	44	11	14	Who shall tell you words, whereby you and all your house shall be saved.
B044C011V015	44	11	15	And as I began to speak, the Holy Ghost fell on them, as on us at the beginning.
B044C011V016	44	11	16	Then remembered I the word of the Lord, that he said, 
B044C011V017	44	11	17	Since God gave them the like gift as he did unto us, who believed on the Lord Jesus Christ; what was I, that I could withstand God?
B044C011V018	44	11	18	When they heard these things, they held their peace, and glorified God, saying, Then has God also to the Gentiles granted repentance unto life.
B044C011V019	44	11	19	Now they which were scattered abroad upon the persecution that arose about Stephen travelled as far as Phenice, and Cyprus, and Antioch, preaching the word to none but unto the Jews only.
B044C011V020	44	11	20	And some of them were men of Cyprus and Cyrene, which, when they had come to Antioch, spoke unto the Grecians, preaching the LORD Jesus.
B044C011V021	44	11	21	And the hand of the Lord was with them: and a great number believed, and turned unto the Lord.
B044C011V022	44	11	22	Then tidings of these things came unto the ears of the church which was in Jerusalem: and they sent forth Barnabas, that he should go as far as Antioch.
B044C011V023	44	11	23	Who, when he came, and had seen the grace of God, was glad, and exhorted them all, that with purpose of heart they would cleave unto the Lord.
B044C011V024	44	11	24	For he was a good man, and full of the Holy Ghost and of faith: and many people was added unto the Lord.
B044C011V025	44	11	25	Then departed Barnabas to Tarsus, for to seek Saul:
B044C011V026	44	11	26	And when he had found him, he brought him unto Antioch. And it came to pass, that a whole year they assembled themselves with the church, and taught many people. And the disciples were called Christians first in Antioch.
B044C011V027	44	11	27	And in these days came prophets from Jerusalem unto Antioch.
B044C011V028	44	11	28	And there stood up one of them named Agabus, and signified by the Spirit that there should be great dearth throughout all the world: which came to pass in the days of Claudius Caesar.
B044C011V029	44	11	29	Then the disciples, every man according to his ability, determined to send relief unto the brothers which dwelled in Judaea:
B044C011V030	44	11	30	Which also they did, and sent it to the elders by the hands of Barnabas and Saul.
B044C012V001	44	12	1	Now about that time Herod the king stretched forth his hands to vex certain of the church.
B044C012V002	44	12	2	And he killed James the brother of John with the sword.
B044C012V003	44	12	3	And because he saw it pleased the Jews, he proceeded further to take Peter also. (Then were the days of unleavened bread.)
B044C012V004	44	12	4	And when he had apprehended him, he put him in prison, and delivered him to four quaternions of soldiers to keep him; intending after passover to bring him forth to the people.
B044C012V005	44	12	5	Peter therefore was kept in prison: but prayer was made without ceasing of the church unto God for him.
B044C012V006	44	12	6	And when Herod would have brought him forth, the same night Peter was sleeping between two soldiers, bound with two chains: and the keepers before the door kept the prison.
B044C012V007	44	12	7	And, behold, the angel of the Lord came upon him, and a light shined in the prison: and he smote Peter on the side, and raised him up, saying, Arise up quickly. And his chains fell off from his hands.
B044C012V008	44	12	8	And the angel said unto him, Gird yourself, and bind on your sandals. And so he did. And he says unto him, Cast your garment about you, and follow me.
B044C012V009	44	12	9	And he went out, and followed him; and knew not that it was true which was done by the angel; but thought he saw a vision.
B044C012V010	44	12	10	When they were past the first and the second ward, they came unto the iron gate that leads unto the city; which opened to them of his own accord: and they went out, and passed on through one street; and immediately the angel departed from him.
B044C012V011	44	12	11	And when Peter was come to himself, he said, Now I know of a surety, that the LORD has sent his angel, and has delivered me out of the hand of Herod, and from all the expectation of the people of the Jews.
B044C012V012	44	12	12	And when he had considered the thing, he came to the house of Mary the mother of John, whose surname was Mark; where many were gathered together praying.
B044C012V013	44	12	13	And as Peter knocked at the door of the gate, a damsel came to hearken, named Rhoda.
B044C012V014	44	12	14	And when she knew Peter's voice, she opened not the gate for gladness, but ran in, and told how Peter stood before the gate.
B044C012V015	44	12	15	And they said unto her, You are mad. But she constantly affirmed that it was even so. Then said they, It is his angel.
B044C012V016	44	12	16	But Peter continued knocking: and when they had opened the door, and saw him, they were astonished.
B044C012V017	44	12	17	But he, beckoning unto them with the hand to hold their peace, declared unto them how the Lord had brought him out of the prison. And he said, Go show these things unto James, and to the brothers. And he departed, and went into another place.
B044C012V018	44	12	18	Now as soon as it was day, there was no small stir among the soldiers, what was become of Peter.
B044C012V019	44	12	19	And when Herod had sought for him, and found him not, he examined the keepers, and commanded that they should be put to death. And he went down from Judaea to Caesarea, and there abode.
B044C012V020	44	12	20	And Herod was highly displeased with them of Tyre and Sidon: but they came with one accord to him, and, having made Blastus the king's chamberlain their friend, desired peace; because their country was nourished by the king's country.
B044C012V021	44	12	21	And upon a set day Herod, arrayed in royal apparel, sat upon his throne, and made an oration unto them.
B044C012V022	44	12	22	And the people gave a shout, saying, It is the voice of a god, and not of a man.
B044C012V023	44	12	23	And immediately the angel of the Lord smote him, because he gave not God the glory: and he was eaten of worms, and gave up the ghost.
B044C012V024	44	12	24	But the word of God grew and multiplied.
B044C012V025	44	12	25	And Barnabas and Saul returned from Jerusalem, when they had fulfilled their ministry, and took with them John, whose surname was Mark.
B044C013V001	44	13	1	Now there were in the church that was at Antioch certain prophets and teachers; as Barnabas, and Simeon that was called Niger, and Lucius of Cyrene, and Manaen, which had been brought up with Herod the tetrarch, and Saul.
B044C013V002	44	13	2	As they ministered to the Lord, and fasted, the Holy Ghost said, Separate me Barnabas and Saul for the work whereunto I have called them.
B044C013V003	44	13	3	And when they had fasted and prayed, and laid their hands on them, they sent them away.
B044C013V004	44	13	4	So they, being sent forth by the Holy Ghost, departed unto Seleucia; and from there they sailed to Cyprus.
B044C013V005	44	13	5	And when they were at Salamis, they preached the word of God in the synagogues of the Jews: and they had also John to their minister.
B044C013V006	44	13	6	And when they had gone through the isle unto Paphos, they found a certain sorcerer, a false prophet, a Jew, whose name was Barjesus:
B044C013V007	44	13	7	Which was with the deputy of the country, Sergius Paulus, a prudent man; who called for Barnabas and Saul, and desired to hear the word of God.
B044C013V008	44	13	8	But Elymas the sorcerer (for so is his name by interpretation) withstood them, seeking to turn away the deputy from the faith.
B044C013V009	44	13	9	Then Saul, (who also is called Paul,) filled with the Holy Ghost, set his eyes on him.
B044C013V010	44	13	10	And said, O full of all trickery and all mischief, you child of the devil, you enemy of all righteousness, will you not cease to pervert the right ways of the Lord?
B044C013V011	44	13	11	And now, behold, the hand of the Lord is upon you, and you shall be blind, not seeing the sun for a season. And immediately there fell on him a mist and a darkness; and he went about seeking some to lead him by the hand.
B044C013V012	44	13	12	Then the deputy, when he saw what was done, believed, being astonished at the doctrine of the Lord.
B044C013V013	44	13	13	Now when Paul and his company loosed from Paphos, they came to Perga in Pamphylia: and John departing from them returned to Jerusalem.
B044C013V014	44	13	14	But when they departed from Perga, they came to Antioch in Pisidia, and went into the synagogue on the sabbath day, and sat down.
B044C013V015	44	13	15	And after the reading of the law and the prophets the rulers of the synagogue sent unto them, saying, You men and brothers, if you have any word of exhortation for the people, say on.
B044C013V016	44	13	16	Then Paul stood up, and beckoning with his hand said, Men of Israel, and you that fear God, give audience.
B044C013V017	44	13	17	The God of this people of Israel chose our fathers, and exalted the people when they dwelled as strangers in the land of Egypt, and with a high arm brought he them out of it.
B044C013V018	44	13	18	And about the time of forty years suffered he their manners in the wilderness.
B044C013V019	44	13	19	And when he had destroyed seven nations in the land of Chanaan, he divided their land to them by lot.
B044C013V020	44	13	20	And after that he gave unto them judges about the space of four hundred and fifty years, until Samuel the prophet.
B044C013V021	44	13	21	And afterward they desired a king: and God gave unto them Saul the son of Cis, a man of the tribe of Benjamin, by the space of forty years.
B044C013V022	44	13	22	And when he had removed him, he raised up unto them David to be their king; to whom also he gave their testimony, and said, I have found David the son of Jesse, a man after my own heart, which shall fulfill all my will.
B044C013V023	44	13	23	Of this man's seed has God according to his promise raised unto Israel a Saviour, Jesus:
B044C013V024	44	13	24	When John had first preached before his coming the baptism of repentance to all the people of Israel.
B044C013V025	44	13	25	And as John fulfilled his course, he said, Whom think you that I am? I am not he. But, behold, there comes one after me, whose shoes of his feet I am not worthy to loose.
B044C013V026	44	13	26	Men and brothers, children of the stock of Abraham, and whosoever among you fears God, to you is the word of this salvation sent.
B044C013V027	44	13	27	For they that dwell at Jerusalem, and their rulers, because they knew him not, nor yet the voices of the prophets which are read every sabbath day, they have fulfilled them in condemning him.
B044C013V028	44	13	28	And though they found no cause of death in him, yet desired they Pilate that he should be slain.
B044C013V029	44	13	29	And when they had fulfilled all that was written of him, they took him down from the tree, and laid him in a sepulcher.
B044C013V030	44	13	30	But God raised him from the dead:
B044C013V031	44	13	31	And he was seen many days of those who came up with him from Galilee to Jerusalem, who are his witnesses unto the people.
B044C013V032	44	13	32	And we declare unto you glad tidings, that the promise which was made unto the fathers,
B044C013V033	44	13	33	God has fulfilled the same unto us their children, in that he has raised up Jesus again; as it is also written in the second psalm, You are my Son, this day have I begotten you.
B044C013V034	44	13	34	And as concerning that he raised him up from the dead, now no more to return to corruption, he said on this wise, I will give you the sure mercies of David.
B044C013V035	44	13	35	Therefore he says also in another psalm, You shall not permit your Holy One to see corruption.
B044C013V036	44	13	36	For David, after he had served his own generation by the will of God, fell on sleep, and was laid unto his fathers, and saw corruption:
B044C013V037	44	13	37	But he, whom God raised again, saw no corruption.
B044C013V038	44	13	38	Be it known unto you therefore, men and brothers, that through this man is preached unto you the forgiveness of sins:
B044C013V039	44	13	39	And by him all that believe are justified from all things, from which you could not be justified by the law of Moses.
B044C013V040	44	13	40	Beware therefore, lest that come upon you, which is spoken of in the prophets;
B044C013V041	44	13	41	Behold, you despisers, and wonder, and perish: for I work a work in your days, a work which you shall in no way believe, though a man declare it unto you.
B044C013V042	44	13	42	And when the Jews were gone out of the synagogue, the Gentiles asked that these words might be preached to them the next sabbath.
B044C013V043	44	13	43	Now when the congregation was broken up, many of the Jews and religious proselytes followed Paul and Barnabas: who, speaking to them, persuaded them to continue in the grace of God.
B044C013V044	44	13	44	And the next sabbath day came almost the whole city together to hear the word of God.
B044C013V045	44	13	45	But when the Jews saw the multitudes, they were filled with envy, and spoke against those things which were spoken by Paul, contradicting and blaspheming.
B044C013V046	44	13	46	Then Paul and Barnabas grown bold, and said, It was necessary that the word of God should first have been spoken to you: but seeing you put it from you, and judge yourselves unworthy of everlasting life, lo, we turn to the Gentiles.
B044C013V047	44	13	47	For so has the Lord commanded us, saying, I have set you to be a light of the Gentiles, that you should be for salvation unto the ends of the earth.
B044C013V048	44	13	48	And when the Gentiles heard this, they were glad, and glorified the word of the Lord: and as many as were ordained to eternal life believed.
B044C013V049	44	13	49	And the word of the Lord was spoken out throughout all the region.
B044C013V050	44	13	50	But the Jews stirred up the devout and honorable women, and the chief men of the city, and raised persecution against Paul and Barnabas, and expelled them out of their borders.
B044C013V051	44	13	51	But they shook off the dust of their feet against them, and came unto Iconium.
B044C013V052	44	13	52	And the disciples were filled with joy, and with the Holy Ghost.
B044C014V001	44	14	1	And it came to pass in Iconium, that they went both together into the synagogue of the Jews, and so spoke, that a great multitude both of the Jews and also of the Greeks believed.
B044C014V002	44	14	2	But the unbelieving Jews stirred up the Gentiles, and made their minds evil affected against the brothers.
B044C014V003	44	14	3	Long time therefore abode they speaking boldly in the Lord, which gave testimony unto the word of his grace, and granted signs and wonders to be done by their hands.
B044C014V004	44	14	4	But the multitude of the city was divided: and part held with the Jews, and part with the apostles.
B044C014V005	44	14	5	And when there was an assault made both of the Gentiles, and also of the Jews with their rulers, to use them despitefully, and to stone them,
B044C014V006	44	14	6	They were ware of it, and fled unto Lystra and Derbe, cities of Lycaonia, and unto the region that lies round about:
B044C014V007	44	14	7	And there they preached the gospel.
B044C014V008	44	14	8	And there sat a certain man at Lystra, sick in his feet, being a cripple from his mother's womb, who never had walked:
B044C014V009	44	14	9	The same heard Paul speak: who steadfastly beholding him, and perceiving that he had faith to be healed,
B044C014V010	44	14	10	Said with a loud voice, Stand upright on your feet. And he leaped and walked.
B044C014V011	44	14	11	And when the people saw what Paul had done, they lifted up their voices, saying in the speech of Lycaonia, The gods are come down to us in the likeness of men.
B044C014V012	44	14	12	And they called Barnabas, Jupiter; and Paul, Mercurius, because he was the chief speaker.
B044C014V013	44	14	13	Then the priest of Jupiter, which was before their city, brought oxen and garlands unto the gates, and would have done sacrifice with the people.
B044C014V014	44	14	14	Which when the apostles, Barnabas and Paul, heard of, they tear their clothes, and ran in among the people, crying out,
B044C014V015	44	14	15	And saying, Sirs, why do you these things? We also are men of like passions with you, and preach unto you that you should turn from these vanities unto the living God, which made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all things that are in it:
B044C014V016	44	14	16	Who in times past permitted all nations to walk in their own ways.
B044C014V017	44	14	17	Nevertheless he left not himself without witness, in that he did good, and gave us rain from heaven, and fruitful seasons, filling our hearts with food and gladness.
B044C014V018	44	14	18	And with these sayings scarce restrained they the people, that they had not done sacrifice unto them.
B044C014V019	44	14	19	And there came to there certain Jews from Antioch and Iconium, who persuaded the people, and having stoned Paul, drew him out of the city, supposing he had been dead.
B044C014V020	44	14	20	Howbeit, as the disciples stood round about him, he rose up, and came into the city: and the next day he departed with Barnabas to Derbe.
B044C014V021	44	14	21	And when they had preached the gospel to that city, and had taught many, they returned again to Lystra, and to Iconium, and Antioch,
B044C014V022	44	14	22	Confirming the souls of the disciples, and exhorting them to continue in the faith, and that we must through much tribulation enter into the kingdom of God.
B044C014V023	44	14	23	And when they had ordained them elders in every church, and had prayed with fasting, they commended them to the Lord, on whom they believed.
B044C014V024	44	14	24	And after they had passed throughout Pisidia, they came to Pamphylia.
B044C014V025	44	14	25	And when they had preached the word in Perga, they went down into Attalia:
B044C014V026	44	14	26	And from there sailed to Antioch, from where they ha been recommended to the grace of God for the work which they fulfilled.
B044C014V027	44	14	27	And when they had come, and had gathered the church together, they rehearsed all that God had done with them, and how he had opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles.
B044C014V028	44	14	28	And there they abode long time with the disciples.
B044C015V001	44	15	1	And certain men which came down from Judaea taught the brothers, and said, Unless you be circumcised after the manner of Moses, you cannot be saved.
B044C015V002	44	15	2	When therefore Paul and Barnabas had no small dissension and disputation with them, they determined that Paul and Barnabas, and certain other of them, should go up to Jerusalem unto the apostles and elders about this question.
B044C015V003	44	15	3	And being brought on their way by the church, they passed through Phenice and Samaria, declaring the conversion of the Gentiles: and they caused great joy unto all the brothers.
B044C015V004	44	15	4	And when they had come to Jerusalem, they were received of the church, and of the apostles and elders, and they declared all things that God had done with them.
B044C015V005	44	15	5	But there rose up certain of the sect of the Pharisees which believed, saying, That it was necessary to circumcise them, and to command them to keep the law of Moses.
B044C015V006	44	15	6	And the apostles and elders came together for to consider of this matter.
B044C015V007	44	15	7	And when there had been much disputing, Peter rose up, and said unto them, Men and brothers, you know that a good while ago God made choice among us, that the Gentiles by my mouth should hear the word of the gospel, and believe.
B044C015V008	44	15	8	And God, which knows the hearts, bore them witness, giving them the Holy Ghost, just as he did unto us;
B044C015V009	44	15	9	And put no difference between us and them, purifying their hearts by faith.
B044C015V010	44	15	10	Now therefore why tempt you God, to put a yoke upon the neck of the disciples, which neither our fathers nor we were able to bear?
B044C015V011	44	15	11	But we believe that through the grace of the LORD Jesus Christ we shall be saved, just as they.
B044C015V012	44	15	12	Then all the multitude kept silence, and gave audience to Barnabas and Paul, declaring what miracles and wonders God had wrought among the Gentiles by them.
B044C015V013	44	15	13	And after they had held their peace, James answered, saying, Men and brothers, hearken unto me:
B044C015V014	44	15	14	Simeon has declared how God at the first did visit the Gentiles, to take out of them a people for his name.
B044C015V015	44	15	15	And to this agree the words of the prophets; as it is written,
B044C015V016	44	15	16	After this I will return, and will build again the tabernacle of David, which is fallen down; and I will build again the ruins of it, and I will set it up:
B044C015V017	44	15	17	That the residue of men might seek after the Lord, and all the Gentiles, upon whom my name is called, says the Lord, who does all these things.
B044C015V018	44	15	18	Known unto God are all his works from the beginning of the world.
B044C015V019	44	15	19	Therefore my sentence is, that we trouble not them, which from among the Gentiles are turned to God:
B044C015V020	44	15	20	But that we write unto them, that they abstain from pollutions of idols, and from fornication, and from things strangled, and from blood.
B044C015V021	44	15	21	For Moses of old time has in every city them that preach him, being read in the synagogues every sabbath day.
B044C015V022	44	15	22	Then pleased it the apostles and elders with the whole church, to send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas; namely, Judas surnamed Barsabas and Silas, chief men among the brothers:
B044C015V023	44	15	23	And they wrote letters by them after this manner; The apostles and elders and brothers send greeting unto the brothers which are of the Gentiles in Antioch and Syria and Cilicia.
B044C015V024	44	15	24	Since as we have heard, that certain which went out from us have troubled you with words, subverting your souls, saying, You must be circumcised, and keep the law: to whom we gave no such commandment:
B044C015V025	44	15	25	It seemed good unto us, being assembled with one accord, to send chosen men unto you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,
B044C015V026	44	15	26	Men that have hazarded their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B044C015V027	44	15	27	We have sent therefore Judas and Silas, who shall also tell you the same things by mouth.
B044C015V028	44	15	28	For it seemed good to the Holy Ghost, and to us, to lay upon you no greater burden than these necessary things;
B044C015V029	44	15	29	That you abstain from foods offered to idols, and from blood, and from things strangled, and from fornication: from which if you keep yourselves, you shall do well. Fare you well.
B044C015V030	44	15	30	So when they were dismissed, they came to Antioch: and when they had gathered the multitude together, they delivered the epistle:
B044C015V031	44	15	31	Which when they had read, they rejoiced for the consolation.
B044C015V032	44	15	32	And Judas and Silas, being prophets also themselves, exhorted the brothers with many words, and confirmed them.
B044C015V033	44	15	33	And after they had tarried there a space, they were let go in peace from the brothers unto the apostles.
B044C015V034	44	15	34	Notwithstanding it pleased Silas to abide there still.
B044C015V035	44	15	35	Paul also and Barnabas continued in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of the Lord, with many others also.
B044C015V036	44	15	36	And some days after Paul said unto Barnabas, Let us go again and visit our brothers in every city where we have preached the word of the LORD, and see how they do.
B044C015V037	44	15	37	And Barnabas determined to take with them John, whose surname was Mark.
B044C015V038	44	15	38	But Paul thought not good to take him with them, who departed from them from Pamphylia, and went not with them to the work.
B044C015V039	44	15	39	And the contention was so sharp between them, that they departed asunder one from the other: and so Barnabas took Mark, and sailed unto Cyprus;
B044C015V040	44	15	40	And Paul chose Silas, and departed, being recommended by the brothers unto the grace of God.
B044C015V041	44	15	41	And he went through Syria and Cilicia, confirming the churches.
B044C016V001	44	16	1	Then came he to Derbe and Lystra: and, behold, a certain disciple was there, named Timotheus, the son of a certain woman, which was a Jewess, and believed; but his father was a Greek:
B044C016V002	44	16	2	Which was well reported of by the brothers that were at Lystra and Iconium.
B044C016V003	44	16	3	Him would Paul have to go forth with him; and took and circumcised him because of the Jews which were in those quarters: for they knew all that his father was a Greek.
B044C016V004	44	16	4	And as they went through the cities, they delivered them the decrees for to keep, that were ordained of the apostles and elders which were at Jerusalem.
B044C016V005	44	16	5	And so were the churches established in the faith, and increased in number daily.
B044C016V006	44	16	6	Now when they had gone throughout Phrygia and the region of Galatia, and were forbidden of the Holy Ghost to preach the word in Asia,
B044C016V007	44	16	7	After they had come to Mysia, they attempted to go into Bithynia: but the Spirit permitted them not.
B044C016V008	44	16	8	And they passing by Mysia came down to Troas.
B044C016V009	44	16	9	And a vision appeared to Paul in the night; There stood a man of Macedonia, and prayed him, saying, Come over into Macedonia, and help us.
B044C016V010	44	16	10	And after he had seen the vision, immediately we endeavored to go into Macedonia, assuredly gathering that the Lord had called us for to preach the gospel unto them.
B044C016V011	44	16	11	Therefore loosing from Troas, we came with a straight course to Samothracia, and the next day to Neapolis;
B044C016V012	44	16	12	And from there to Philippi, which is the chief city of that part of Macedonia, and a colony: and we were in that city abiding certain days.
B044C016V013	44	16	13	And on the sabbath we went out of the city by a river side, where prayer was accustomed to be made; and we sat down, and spoke unto the women which resorted to there.
B044C016V014	44	16	14	And a certain woman named Lydia, a seller of purple, of the city of Youratira, which worshipped God, heard us: whose heart the Lord opened, that she attended unto the things which were spoken of Paul.
B044C016V015	44	16	15	And when she was baptized, and her household, she asked us, saying, If you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come into my house, and abide there. And she constrained us.
B044C016V016	44	16	16	And it came to pass, as we went to prayer, a certain damsel possessed with a spirit of divination met us, which brought her masters much gain by soothsaying:
B044C016V017	44	16	17	The same followed Paul and us, and cried, saying, These men are the servants of the most high God, which show unto us the way of salvation.
B044C016V018	44	16	18	And this did she many days. But Paul, being grieved, turned and said to the spirit, I command you in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her. And he came out the same hour.
B044C016V019	44	16	19	And when her masters saw that the hope of their gains was gone, they caught Paul and Silas, and drew them into the marketplace unto the rulers,
B044C016V020	44	16	20	And brought them to the magistrates, saying, These men, being Jews, do exceedingly trouble our city,
B044C016V021	44	16	21	And teach customs, which are not lawful for us to receive, neither to observe, being Romans.
B044C016V022	44	16	22	And the multitude rose up together against them: and the magistrates tore off their clothes, and commanded to beat them.
B044C016V023	44	16	23	And when they had laid many stripes upon them, they cast them into prison, charging the jailer to keep them safely:
B044C016V024	44	16	24	Who, having received such a charge, thrust them into the inner prison, and made their feet fast in the stocks.
B044C016V025	44	16	25	And at midnight Paul and Silas prayed, and sang praises unto God: and the prisoners heard them.
B044C016V026	44	16	26	And suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of the prison were shaken: and immediately all the doors were opened, and every one's bands were loosed.
B044C016V027	44	16	27	And the keeper of the prison awaking out of his sleep, and seeing the prison doors open, he drew out his sword, and would have killed himself, supposing that the prisoners had been fled.
B044C016V028	44	16	28	But Paul cried with a loud voice, saying, Do yourself no harm: for we are all here.
B044C016V029	44	16	29	Then he called for a light, and sprang in, and came trembling, and fell down before Paul and Silas,
B044C016V030	44	16	30	And brought them out, and said, Sirs, what must I do to be saved?
B044C016V031	44	16	31	And they said, Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and you shall be saved, and your house.
B044C016V032	44	16	32	And they spoke unto him the word of the Lord, and to all that were in his house.
B044C016V033	44	16	33	And he took them the same hour of the night, and washed their stripes; and was baptized, he and all his, immediately.
B044C016V034	44	16	34	And when he had brought them into his house, he set food before them, and rejoiced, believing in God with all his house.
B044C016V035	44	16	35	And when it was day, the magistrates sent the sergeants, saying, Let those men go.
B044C016V036	44	16	36	And the keeper of the prison told this saying to Paul, The magistrates have sent to let you go: now therefore depart, and go in peace.
B044C016V037	44	16	37	But Paul said unto them, They have beaten us openly uncondemned, being Romans, and have cast us into prison; and now do they thrust us out secretly? no truthfully; but let them come themselves and fetch us out.
B044C016V038	44	16	38	And the sergeants told these words unto the magistrates: and they feared, when they heard that they were Romans.
B044C016V039	44	16	39	And they came and sought them, and brought them out, and desired them to depart out of the city.
B044C016V040	44	16	40	And they went out of the prison, and entered into the house of Lydia: and when they had seen the brothers, they comforted them, and departed.
B044C017V001	44	17	1	Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica, where was a synagogue of the Jews:
B044C017V002	44	17	2	And Paul, as his manner was, went in unto them, and three sabbath days reasoned with them out of the scriptures,
B044C017V003	44	17	3	Opening and alleging, that Christ must needs have suffered, and risen again from the dead; and that this Jesus, whom I preach unto you, is Christ.
B044C017V004	44	17	4	And some of them believed, and consorted with Paul and Silas; and of the devout Greeks a great multitude, and of the chief women not a few.
B044C017V005	44	17	5	But the Jews which believed not, moved with envy, took unto them certain lewd fellows of the baser sort, and gathered a company, and set all the city on an uproar, and assaulted the house of Jason, and sought to bring them out to the people.
B044C017V006	44	17	6	And when they found them not, they drew Jason and certain brothers unto the rulers of the city, crying, These that have turned the world upside down are come to here also;
B044C017V007	44	17	7	Whom Jason has received: and these all do contrary to the decrees of Caesar, saying that there is another king, one Jesus.
B044C017V008	44	17	8	And they troubled the people and the rulers of the city, when they heard these things.
B044C017V009	44	17	9	And when they had taken security of Jason, and of the other, they let them go.
B044C017V010	44	17	10	And the brothers immediately sent away Paul and Silas by night unto Berea: who coming to there went into the synagogue of the Jews.
B044C017V011	44	17	11	These were more noble than those in Thessalonica, in that they received the word with all readiness of mind, and searched the scriptures daily, whether those things were so.
B044C017V012	44	17	12	Therefore many of them believed; also of honorable women which were Greeks, and of men, not a few.
B044C017V013	44	17	13	But when the Jews of Thessalonica had knowledge that the word of God was preached of Paul at Berea, they came to there also, and stirred up the people.
B044C017V014	44	17	14	And then immediately the brothers sent away Paul to go as it were to the sea: but Silas and Timotheus abode there still.
B044C017V015	44	17	15	And they that conducted Paul brought him unto Athens: and receiving a commandment unto Silas and Timotheus for to come to him with all speed, they departed.
B044C017V016	44	17	16	Now while Paul waited for them at Athens, his spirit was stirred in him, when he saw the city wholly given to idolatry.
B044C017V017	44	17	17	Therefore disputed he in the synagogue with the Jews, and with the devout persons, and in the market daily with them that met with him.
B044C017V018	44	17	18	Then certain philosophers of the Epicureans, and of the Stoicks, encountered him. And some said, What will this babbler say? other some, He seems to be a setter forth of strange gods: because he preached unto them Jesus, and the resurrection.
B044C017V019	44	17	19	And they took him, and brought him unto Areopagus, saying, May we know what this new doctrine, whereof you speak, is?
B044C017V020	44	17	20	For you bring certain strange things to our ears: we would know therefore what these things mean.
B044C017V021	44	17	21	(For all the Athenians and strangers which were there spent their time in nothing else, but either to tell, or to hear some new thing.)
B044C017V022	44	17	22	Then Paul stood in the midst of Mars' hill, and said, You men of Athens, I perceive that in all things you are too superstitious.
B044C017V023	44	17	23	For as I passed by, and beheld your devotions, I found an altar with this inscription, TO THE UNKNOWN GOD. Whom therefore you ignorantly worship, him declare I unto you.
B044C017V024	44	17	24	God that made the world and all things in it, seeing that he is Lord of heaven and earth, dwells not in temples made with hands;
B044C017V025	44	17	25	Neither is worshipped with men's hands, as though he needed any thing, seeing he gives to all life, and breath, and all things;
B044C017V026	44	17	26	And has made of one blood all nations of men for to dwell on all the face of the earth, and has determined the times before appointed, and the bounds of their habitation;
B044C017V027	44	17	27	That they should seek the Lord, if haply they might feel after him, and find him, though he be not far from every one of us:
B044C017V028	44	17	28	For in him we live, and move, and have our being; as certain also of your own poets have said, For we are also his offspring.
B044C017V029	44	17	29	Since we are the offspring of God, we ought not to think that the Godhead is like unto gold, or silver, or stone, graven by are and man's device.
B044C017V030	44	17	30	And the times of this ignorance God winked at; but now commands all men every where to repent:
B044C017V031	44	17	31	Because he has appointed a day, in which he will judge the world in righteousness by that man whom he has ordained; whereof he has given assurance unto all men, in that he has raised him from the dead.
B044C017V032	44	17	32	And when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked: and others said, We will hear you again of this matter.
B044C017V033	44	17	33	So Paul departed from among them.
B044C017V034	44	17	34	Howbeit certain men clave unto him, and believed: among the which was Dionysius the Areopagite, and a woman named Damaris, and others with them.
B044C018V001	44	18	1	After these things Paul departed from Athens, and came to Corinth;
B044C018V002	44	18	2	And found a certain Jew named Aquila, born in Pontus, lately come from Italy, with his wife Priscilla; (because Claudius had commanded all Jews to depart from Rome:) and came unto them.
B044C018V003	44	18	3	And because he was of the same craft, he abode with them, and wrought: for by their occupation they were tentmakers.
B044C018V004	44	18	4	And he reasoned in the synagogue every sabbath, and persuaded the Jews and the Greeks.
B044C018V005	44	18	5	And when Silas and Timotheus had come from Macedonia, Paul was pressed in the spirit, and testified to the Jews that Jesus was Christ.
B044C018V006	44	18	6	And when they opposed themselves, and blasphemed, he shook his clothing, and said unto them, Your blood be upon your own heads; I am clean; from now on I will go unto the Gentiles.
B044C018V007	44	18	7	And he departed from there, and entered into a certain man's house, named Justus, one that worshipped God, whose house joined hard to the synagogue.
B044C018V008	44	18	8	And Crispus, the chief ruler of the synagogue, believed on the Lord with all his house; and many of the Corinthians hearing believed, and were baptized.
B044C018V009	44	18	9	Then spoke the Lord to Paul in the night by a vision, 
B044C018V010	44	18	10	
        
B044C018V011	44	18	11	And he continued there a year and six months, teaching the word of God among them.
B044C018V012	44	18	12	And when Gallio was the deputy of Achaia, the Jews made insurrection with one accord against Paul, and brought him to the judgment seat,
B044C018V013	44	18	13	Saying, This fellow persuades men to worship God contrary to the law.
B044C018V014	44	18	14	And when Paul was now about to open his mouth, Gallio said unto the Jews, If it were a matter of wrong or wicked lewdness, O you Jews, reason would that I should bear with you:
B044C018V015	44	18	15	But if it be a question of words and names, and of your law, look you to it; for I will be no judge of such matters.
B044C018V016	44	18	16	And he drove them from the judgment seat.
B044C018V017	44	18	17	Then all the Greeks took Sosthenes, the chief ruler of the synagogue, and beat him before the judgment seat. And Gallio cared for none of those things.
B044C018V018	44	18	18	And Paul after this tarried there yet a good while, and then took his leave of the brothers, and sailed from there into Syria, and with him Priscilla and Aquila; having shorn his head in Cenchrea: for he had a vow.
B044C018V019	44	18	19	And he came to Ephesus, and left them there: but he himself entered into the synagogue, and reasoned with the Jews.
B044C018V020	44	18	20	When they desired him to tarry longer time with them, he consented not;
B044C018V021	44	18	21	But bade them farewell, saying, I must by all means keep this feast that comes in Jerusalem: but I will return again unto you, if God will. And he sailed from Ephesus.
B044C018V022	44	18	22	And when he had landed at Caesarea, and gone up, and saluted the church, he went down to Antioch.
B044C018V023	44	18	23	And after he had spent some time there, he departed, and went over all the country of Galatia and Phrygia in order, strengthening all the disciples.
B044C018V024	44	18	24	And a certain Jew named Apollos, born at Alexandria, an eloquent man, and mighty in the scriptures, came to Ephesus.
B044C018V025	44	18	25	This man was instructed on the way of the Lord; and being fervent in the spirit, he spoke and taught diligently the things of the Lord, knowing only the baptism of John.
B044C018V026	44	18	26	And he began to speak boldly in the synagogue: whom when Aquila and Priscilla had heard, they took him unto them, and expounded unto him the way of God more perfectly.
B044C018V027	44	18	27	And when he was disposed to pass into Achaia, the brothers wrote, exhorting the disciples to receive him: who, when he was come, helped them much which had believed through grace:
B044C018V028	44	18	28	For he mightily convinced the Jews, and that publicly, showing by the scriptures that Jesus was Christ.
B044C019V001	44	19	1	And it came to pass, that, while Apollos was at Corinth, Paul having passed through the upper borders came to Ephesus: and finding certain disciples,
B044C019V002	44	19	2	He said unto them, Have you received the Holy Ghost since you believed? And they said unto him, We have not so much as heard whether there be any Holy Ghost.
B044C019V003	44	19	3	And he said unto them, Unto what then were you baptized? And they said, Unto John's baptism.
B044C019V004	44	19	4	Then said Paul, John truthfully baptized with the baptism of repentance, saying unto the people, that they should believe on him which should come after him, that is, on Christ Jesus.
B044C019V005	44	19	5	When they heard this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C019V006	44	19	6	And when Paul had laid his hands upon them, the Holy Ghost came on them; and they spoke with tongues, and prophesied.
B044C019V007	44	19	7	And all the men were about twelve.
B044C019V008	44	19	8	And he went into the synagogue, and spoke boldly for the space of three months, disputing and persuading the things concerning the kingdom of God.
B044C019V009	44	19	9	But when different were hardened, and believed not, but spoke evil of that way before the multitude, he departed from them, and separated the disciples, disputing daily in the school of one Tyrannus.
B044C019V010	44	19	10	And this continued by the space of two years; so that all they which dwelled in Asia heard the word of the Lord Jesus, both Jews and Greeks.
B044C019V011	44	19	11	And God wrought special miracles by the hands of Paul:
B044C019V012	44	19	12	So that from his body were brought unto the sick handkerchiefs or aprons, and the diseases departed from them, and the evil spirits went out of them.
B044C019V013	44	19	13	Then certain of the vagabond Jews, exorcists, took upon them to call over those who had evil spirits the name of the LORD Jesus, saying, We adjure you by Jesus whom Paul preacheth.
B044C019V014	44	19	14	And there were seven sons of one Sceva, a Jew, and chief of the priests, which did so.
B044C019V015	44	19	15	And the evil spirit answered and said, Jesus I know, and Paul I know; but who are you?
B044C019V016	44	19	16	And the man in whom the evil spirit was leaped on them, and overcame them, and prevailed against them, so that they fled out of that house naked and wounded.
B044C019V017	44	19	17	And this was known to all the Jews and Greeks also dwelling at Ephesus; and fear fell on them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified.
B044C019V018	44	19	18	And many that believed came, and confessed, and showed their deeds.
B044C019V019	44	19	19	Many of them also which used curious arts brought their books together, and burned them before all men: and they counted the price of them, and found it fifty thousand pieces of silver.
B044C019V020	44	19	20	So mightily grew the word of God and prevailed.
B044C019V021	44	19	21	After these things were ended, Paul purposed in the spirit, when he had passed through Macedonia and Achaia, to go to Jerusalem, saying, After I have been there, I must also see Rome.
B044C019V022	44	19	22	So he sent into Macedonia two of them that ministered unto him, Timotheus and Erastus; but he himself stayed in Asia for a season.
B044C019V023	44	19	23	And the same time there arose no small stir about that way.
B044C019V024	44	19	24	For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, which made silver shrines for Diana, brought no small gain unto the craftsmen;
B044C019V025	44	19	25	Whom he called together with the workmen of like occupation, and said, Sirs, you know that by this craft we have our wealth.
B044C019V026	44	19	26	Moreover you see and hear, that not alone at Ephesus, but almost throughout all Asia, this Paul has persuaded and turned away much people, saying that they be no gods, which are made with hands:
B044C019V027	44	19	27	So that not only this our craft is in danger to be set at nought; but also that the temple of the great goddess Diana should be despised, and her magnificence should be destroyed, whom all Asia and the world worships.
B044C019V028	44	19	28	And when they heard these sayings, they were full of wrath, and cried out, saying, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.
B044C019V029	44	19	29	And the whole city was filled with confusion: and having caught Gaius and Aristarchus, men of Macedonia, Paul's companions in travel, they rushed with one accord into the theater.
B044C019V030	44	19	30	And when Paul would have entered in unto the people, the disciples did not permit.
B044C019V031	44	19	31	And certain of the chief of Asia, which were his friends, sent unto him, desiring him that he would not adventure himself into the theater.
B044C019V032	44	19	32	Some therefore cried one thing, and some another: for the assembly was confused: and the more part did not know why they were come together.
B044C019V033	44	19	33	And they drew Alexander out of the multitude, the Jews putting him forward. And Alexander beckoned with the hand, and would have made his defense unto the people.
B044C019V034	44	19	34	But when they knew that he was a Jew, all with one voice about the space of two hours cried out, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.
B044C019V035	44	19	35	And when the town clerk had appeased the people, he said, You men of Ephesus, what man is there that knows not that the city of the Ephesians is a worshiper of the great goddess Diana, and of the image which fell down from Jupiter?
B044C019V036	44	19	36	Seeing then that these things cannot be spoken against, you ought to be quiet, and to do nothing rashly.
B044C019V037	44	19	37	For you have brought to here these men, which are neither robbers of churches, nor yet blasphemers of your goddess.
B044C019V038	44	19	38	Therefore if Demetrius, and the craftsmen which are with him, have a matter against any man, the law is open, and there are deputies: let them plead with one another.
B044C019V039	44	19	39	But if you inquire any thing concerning other matters, it shall be determined in a lawful assembly.
B044C019V040	44	19	40	For we are in danger to be called in question for this day's uproar, there being no cause whereby we may give an account of this concourse.
B044C019V041	44	19	41	And when he had thus spoken, he dismissed the assembly.
B044C020V001	44	20	1	And after the uproar was ceased, Paul called unto him the disciples, and embraced them, and departed for to go into Macedonia.
B044C020V002	44	20	2	And when he had gone over those parts, and had given them much exhortation, he came into Greece,
B044C020V003	44	20	3	And there abode three months. And when the Jews laid wait for him, as he was about to sail into Syria, he purposed to return through Macedonia.
B044C020V004	44	20	4	And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus.
B044C020V005	44	20	5	These going before tarried for us at Troas.
B044C020V006	44	20	6	And we sailed away from Philippi after the days of unleavened bread, and came unto them to Troas in five days; where we abode seven days.
B044C020V007	44	20	7	And upon the first day of the week, when the disciples came together to break bread, Paul preached unto them, ready to depart on the next day; and continued his speech until midnight.
B044C020V008	44	20	8	And there were many lights in the upper chamber, where they were gathered together.
B044C020V009	44	20	9	And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, being fallen into a deep sleep: and as Paul was long preaching, he sunk down with sleep, and fell down from the third loft, and was taken up dead.
B044C020V010	44	20	10	And Paul went down, and fell on him, and embracing him said, Trouble not yourselves; for his life is in him.
B044C020V011	44	20	11	When he therefore was come up again, and had broken bread, and eaten, and talked a long while, even till break of day, so he departed.
B044C020V012	44	20	12	And they brought the young man alive, and were not a little comforted.
B044C020V013	44	20	13	And we went before to ship, and sailed unto Assos, there intending to take in Paul: for so had he appointed, minding himself to go on foot.
B044C020V014	44	20	14	And when he met with us at Assos, we took him in, and came to Mitylene.
B044C020V015	44	20	15	And we sailed from there, and came the next day over against Chios; and the next day we arrived at Samos, and tarried at Trogyllium; and the next day we came to Miletus.
B044C020V016	44	20	16	For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus, because he would not spend the time in Asia: for he hasted, if it were possible for him, to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost.
B044C020V017	44	20	17	And from Miletus he sent to Ephesus, and called the elders of the church.
B044C020V018	44	20	18	And when they had come to him, he said unto them, You know, from the first day that I came into Asia, after what manner I have been with you at all seasons,
B044C020V019	44	20	19	Serving the LORD with all humility of mind, and with many tears, and temptations, which befell me by the lying in wait of the Jews:
B044C020V020	44	20	20	And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you, but have showed you, and have taught you publicly, and from house to house,
B044C020V021	44	20	21	Testifying both to the Jews, and also to the Greeks, repentance toward God, and faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ.
B044C020V022	44	20	22	And now, behold, I go bound in the spirit unto Jerusalem, not knowing the things that shall befall me there:
B044C020V023	44	20	23	Save that the Holy Ghost witnesses in every city, saying that bonds and afflictions abide me.
B044C020V024	44	20	24	But none of these things move me, neither count I my life dear unto myself, so that I might finish my course with joy, and the ministry, which I have received of the Lord Jesus, to testify the gospel of the grace of God.
B044C020V025	44	20	25	And now, behold, I know that you all, among whom I have gone preaching the kingdom of God, shall see my face no more.
B044C020V026	44	20	26	Therefore I take you to record this day, that I am pure from the blood of all men.
B044C020V027	44	20	27	For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God.
B044C020V028	44	20	28	Take heed therefore unto yourselves, and to all the flock, over the which the Holy Ghost has made you overseers, to feed the church of God, which he has purchased with his own blood.
B044C020V029	44	20	29	For I know this, that after my departing shall grievous wolves enter in among you, not sparing the flock.
B044C020V030	44	20	30	Also of your own selves shall men arise, speaking perverse things, to draw away disciples after them.
B044C020V031	44	20	31	Therefore watch, and remember, that by the space of three years I ceased not to warn every one night and day with tears.
B044C020V032	44	20	32	And now, brothers, I commend you to God, and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up, and to give you an inheritance among all those who are sanctified.
B044C020V033	44	20	33	I have coveted no man's silver, or gold, or apparel.
B044C020V034	44	20	34	Yes, you yourselves know, that these hands have ministered unto my necessities, and to them that were with me.
B044C020V035	44	20	35	I have showed you all things, that so laboring you ought to support the weak, and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how he said, 
B044C020V036	44	20	36	And when he had thus spoken, he kneeled down, and prayed with them all.
B044C020V037	44	20	37	And they all wept intensely, and fell on Paul's neck, and kissed him,
B044C020V038	44	20	38	Sorrowing most of all for the words which he spoke, that they should see his face no more. And they accompanied him unto the ship.
B044C021V001	44	21	1	And it came to pass, that after we were gotten from them, and had launched, we came with a straight course unto Coos, and the day following unto Rhodes, and from there unto Patara:
B044C021V002	44	21	2	And finding a ship sailing over unto Phenicia, we went aboard, and set forth.
B044C021V003	44	21	3	Now when we had discovered Cyprus, we left it on the left hand, and sailed into Syria, and landed at Tyre: for there the ship was to unload her burden.
B044C021V004	44	21	4	And finding disciples, we tarried there seven days: who said to Paul through the Spirit, that he should not go up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V005	44	21	5	And when we had accomplished those days, we departed and went our way; and they all brought us on our way, with wives and children, till we were out of the city: and we kneeled down on the shore, and prayed.
B044C021V006	44	21	6	And when we had taken our leave one of another, we took ship; and they returned home again.
B044C021V007	44	21	7	And when we had finished our course from Tyre, we came to Ptolemais, and saluted the brothers, and abode with them one day.
B044C021V008	44	21	8	And the next day we that were of Paul's company departed, and came unto Caesarea: and we entered into the house of Philip the evangelist, which was one of the seven; and abode with him.
B044C021V009	44	21	9	And the same man had four daughters, virgins, which did prophesy.
B044C021V010	44	21	10	And as we tarried there many days, there came down from Judaea a certain prophet, named Agabus.
B044C021V011	44	21	11	And when he was come unto us, he took Paul's girdle, and bound his own hands and feet, and said, Thus says the Holy Ghost, So shall the Jews at Jerusalem bind the man that owns this girdle, and shall deliver him into the hands of the Gentiles.
B044C021V012	44	21	12	And when we heard these things, both we, and they of that place, asked him not to go up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V013	44	21	13	Then Paul answered, What mean you to weep and to break mine heart? for I am ready not to be bound only, but also to die at Jerusalem for the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C021V014	44	21	14	And when he would not be persuaded, we ceased, saying, The will of the Lord be done.
B044C021V015	44	21	15	And after those days we took up our carriages, and went up to Jerusalem.
B044C021V016	44	21	16	There went with us also certain of the disciples of Caesarea, and brought with them one Mnason of Cyprus, an old disciple, with whom we should lodge.
B044C021V017	44	21	17	And when we had come to Jerusalem, the brothers received us gladly.
B044C021V018	44	21	18	And the day following Paul went in with us unto James; and all the elders were present.
B044C021V019	44	21	19	And when he had saluted them, he declared particularly what things God had wrought among the Gentiles by his ministry.
B044C021V020	44	21	20	And when they heard it, they glorified the Lord, and said unto him, You see, brother, how many thousands of Jews there are which believe; and they are all zealous of the law:
B044C021V021	44	21	21	And they are informed of you, that you teach all the Jews which are among the Gentiles to forsake Moses, saying that they ought not to circumcise their children, neither to walk after the customs.
B044C021V022	44	21	22	What is it therefore? the multitude must needs come together: for they will hear that you are come.
B044C021V023	44	21	23	Do therefore this that we say to you: We have four men which have a vow on them;
B044C021V024	44	21	24	Them take, and purify yourself with them, and be at charges with them, that they may shave their heads: and all may know that those things, whereof they were informed concerning you, are nothing; but that you yourself also walk orderly, and keep the law.
B044C021V025	44	21	25	As touching the Gentiles which believe, we have written and concluded that they observe no such thing, save only that they keep themselves from things offered to idols, and from blood, and from strangled, and from fornication.
B044C021V026	44	21	26	Then Paul took the men, and the next day purifying himself with them entered into the temple, to signify the accomplishment of the days of purification, until that an offering should be offered for every one of them.
B044C021V027	44	21	27	And when the seven days were almost ended, the Jews which were of Asia, when they saw him in the temple, stirred up all the people, and laid hands on him,
B044C021V028	44	21	28	Crying out, Men of Israel, help: This is the man, that teaches all men every where against the people, and the law, and this place: and further brought Greeks also into the temple, and has polluted this holy place.
B044C021V029	44	21	29	(For they had seen before with him in the city Trophimus an Ephesian, whom they supposed that Paul had brought into the temple.)
B044C021V030	44	21	30	And all the city was moved, and the people ran together: and they took Paul, and drew him out of the temple: and immediately the doors were shut.
B044C021V031	44	21	31	And as they went about to kill him, tidings came unto the chief captain of the band, that all Jerusalem was in an uproar.
B044C021V032	44	21	32	Who immediately took soldiers and centurions, and ran down unto them: and when they saw the chief captain and the soldiers, they left beating of Paul.
B044C021V033	44	21	33	Then the chief captain came near, and took him, and commanded him to be bound with two chains; and demanded who he was, and what he had done.
B044C021V034	44	21	34	And some cried one thing, some another, among the multitude: and when he could not know the certainty for the tumult, he commanded him to be carried into the castle.
B044C021V035	44	21	35	And when he came upon the stairs, so it was, that he was borne of the soldiers for the violence of the people.
B044C021V036	44	21	36	For the multitude of the people followed after, crying, Away with him.
B044C021V037	44	21	37	And as Paul was to be led into the castle, he said unto the chief captain, May I speak unto you? Who said, Can you speak Greek?
