B044C021V039	44	21	39	But Paul said, I am a man who is a Jew of Tarsus, a city in Cilicia, a citizen of no mean city: and, I beseech you, permit me to speak unto the people.
B044C021V040	44	21	40	And when he had given him license, Paul stood on the stairs, and beckoned with the hand unto the people. And when there was made a great silence, he spoke unto them in the Hebrew tongue, saying,
B044C022V001	44	22	1	Men, brothers, and fathers, hear you my defense which I make now unto you.
B044C022V002	44	22	2	(And when they heard that he spoke in the Hebrew tongue to them, they kept the more silence: and he says,)
B044C022V003	44	22	3	I am truthfully a man which am a Jew, born in Tarsus, a city in Cilicia, yet brought up in this city at the feet of Gamaliel, and taught according to the perfect manner of the law of the fathers, and was zealous toward God, as you all are this day.
B044C022V004	44	22	4	And I persecuted this way unto the death, binding and delivering into prisons both men and women.
B044C022V005	44	22	5	As also the high priest does bear me witness, and all the estate of the elders: from whom also I received letters unto the brothers, and went to Damascus, to bring those who were there bound unto Jerusalem, for to be punished.
B044C022V006	44	22	6	And it came to pass, that, as I made my journey, and was come close unto Damascus about noon, suddenly there shone from heaven a great light round about me.
B044C022V007	44	22	7	And I fell unto the ground, and heard a voice saying unto me, 
