B044C022V012	44	22	12	And one Ananias, a devout man according to the law, having a good report of all the Jews which dwelled there,
B044C022V013	44	22	13	Came unto me, and stood, and said unto me, Brother Saul, receive your sight. And the same hour I looked up upon him.
B044C022V014	44	22	14	And he said, The God of our fathers has chosen you, that you should know his will, and see that Just One, and should hear the voice of his mouth.
B044C022V015	44	22	15	For you shall be his witness unto all men of what you have seen and heard.
B044C022V016	44	22	16	And now why do you tarry? arise, and be baptized, and wash away your sins, calling on the name of the Lord.
B044C022V017	44	22	17	And it came to pass, that, when I was come again to Jerusalem, even while I prayed in the temple, I was in a trance;
B044C022V018	44	22	18	And saw him saying unto me, 
