B044C023V035	44	23	35	I will hear you, said he, when your accusers are also come. And he commanded him to be kept in Herod's judgment hall.
B044C024V001	44	24	1	And after five days Ananias the high priest descended with the elders, and with a certain orator named Tertullus, who informed the governor against Paul.
B044C024V002	44	24	2	And when he was called forth, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying, Seeing that by you we enjoy great quietness, and that very worthy deeds are done unto this nation by your providence,
B044C024V003	44	24	3	We accept it always, and in all places, most noble Felix, with all thankfulness.
B044C024V004	44	24	4	Notwithstanding, that I be not further tedious unto you, I pray you that you would hear us of your clemency a few words.
B044C024V005	44	24	5	For we have found this man a pestilent fellow, and a mover of sedition among all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes:
B044C024V006	44	24	6	Who also has gone about to profane the temple: whom we took, and would have judged according to our law.
B044C024V007	44	24	7	But the chief captain Lysias came upon us, and with great violence took him away out of our hands,
B044C024V008	44	24	8	Commanding his accusers to come unto you: by examining of whom yourself may take knowledge of all these things, whereof we accuse him.
B044C024V009	44	24	9	And the Jews also assented, saying that these things were so.
B044C024V010	44	24	10	Then Paul, after the governor had beckoned unto him to speak, answered, Since as I know that you have been of many years a judge unto this nation, I do the more cheerfully answer for myself:
B044C024V011	44	24	11	Because that you may understand, that there are yet but twelve days since I went up to Jerusalem for to worship.
B044C024V012	44	24	12	And they neither found me in the temple disputing with any man, neither raising up the people, neither in the synagogues, nor in the city:
B044C024V013	44	24	13	Neither can they prove the things whereof they now accuse me.
B044C024V014	44	24	14	But this I confess unto you, that after the way which they call heresy, so worship I the God of my fathers, believing all things which are written in the law and in the prophets:
B044C024V015	44	24	15	And have hope toward God, which they themselves also allow, that there shall be a resurrection of the dead, both of the just and unjust.
B044C024V016	44	24	16	And herein do I exercise myself, to have always a conscience void to offense toward God, and toward men.
B044C024V017	44	24	17	Now after many years I came to bring alms to my nation, and offerings.
B044C024V018	44	24	18	Whereupon certain Jews from Asia found me purified in the temple, neither with multitude, nor with tumult.
