B066C004V001	66	4	1	After this I looked, and, behold, a door was opened in heaven: and the first voice which I heard was as it were of a trumpet talking with me; which said, Come up to here, and I will show you things which must be hereafter.
B066C004V002	66	4	2	And immediately I was in the spirit: and, behold, a throne was set in heaven, and one sat on the throne.
B066C004V003	66	4	3	And he that sat was to look upon like a jasper and a sardine stone: and there was a rainbow round about the throne, in sight like unto an emerald.
B066C004V004	66	4	4	And round about the throne were four and twenty seats: and upon the seats I saw four and twenty elders sitting, clothed in white clothing; and they had on their heads crowns of gold.
B066C004V005	66	4	5	And out of the throne proceeded lightnings and thunderings and voices: and there were seven lamps of fire burning before the throne, which are the seven Spirits of God.
B066C004V006	66	4	6	And before the throne there was a sea of glass like unto crystal: and in the midst of the throne, and round about the throne, were four beasts full of eyes before and behind.
B066C004V007	66	4	7	And the first beast was like a lion, and the second beast like a calf, and the third beast had a face as a man, and the fourth beast was like a flying eagle.
B066C004V008	66	4	8	And the four beasts had each of them six wings about him; and they were full of eyes within: and they rest not day and night, saying, Holy, holy, holy, LORD God Almighty, which was, and is, and is to come.
B066C004V009	66	4	9	And when those beasts give glory and honor and thanks to him that sat on the throne, who lives forever and ever,
B066C004V010	66	4	10	The four and twenty elders fall down before him that sat on the throne, and worship him that lives forever and ever, and cast their crowns before the throne, saying,
B066C004V011	66	4	11	You are worthy, O Lord, to receive glory and honor and power: for you have created all things, and for your pleasure they are and were created.
B066C005V001	66	5	1	And I saw in the right hand of him that sat on the throne a book written within and on the backside, sealed with seven seals.
B066C005V002	66	5	2	And I saw a strong angel proclaiming with a loud voice, Who is worthy to open the book, and to loose the seals of it?
B066C005V003	66	5	3	And no man in heaven, nor in earth, neither under the earth, was able to open the book, neither to look thereon.
B066C005V004	66	5	4	And I wept much, because no man was found worthy to open and to read the book, neither to look thereon.
B066C005V005	66	5	5	And one of the elders says unto me, Weep not: behold, the Lion of the tribe of Juda, the Root of David, has prevailed to open the book, and to loose the seven seals of it.
B066C005V006	66	5	6	And I beheld, and, lo, in the midst of the throne and of the four beasts, and in the midst of the elders, stood a Lamb as it had been slain, having seven horns and seven eyes, which are the seven Spirits of God sent forth into all the earth.
B066C005V007	66	5	7	And he came and took the book out of the right hand of him that sat upon the throne.
B066C005V008	66	5	8	And when he had taken the book, the four beasts and four and twenty elders fell down before the Lamb, having every one of them harps, and golden vials full of odors, which are the prayers of saints.
B066C005V009	66	5	9	And they sung a new song, saying, You are worthy to take the book, and to open the seals of it: for you were slain, and have redeemed us to God by your blood out of every kindred, and tongue, and people, and nation;
B066C005V010	66	5	10	And have made us unto our God kings and priests: and we shall reign on the earth.
B066C005V011	66	5	11	And I beheld, and I heard the voice of many angels round about the throne and the beasts and the elders: and the number of them was ten thousand times ten thousand, and thousands of thousands;
B066C005V012	66	5	12	Saying with a loud voice, Worthy is the Lamb that was slain to receive power, and riches, and wisdom, and strength, and honor, and glory, and blessing.
B066C005V013	66	5	13	And every creature which is in heaven, and on the earth, and under the earth, and such as are in the sea, and all that are in them, heard I saying, Blessing, and honor, and glory, and power, be unto him that sits upon the throne, and unto the Lamb forever and ever.
B066C005V014	66	5	14	And the four beasts said, Amen. And the four and twenty elders fell down and worshipped him that lives forever and ever.
B066C006V001	66	6	1	And I saw when the Lamb opened one of the seals, and I heard, as it were the noise of thunder, one of the four beasts saying, Come and see.
B066C006V002	66	6	2	And I saw, and behold a white horse: and he that sat on him had a bow; and a crown was given unto him: and he went forth conquering, and to conquer.
B066C006V003	66	6	3	And when he had opened the second seal, I heard the second beast say, Come and see.
B066C006V004	66	6	4	And there went out another horse that was red: and power was given to him that sat thereon to take peace from the earth, and that they should kill one another: and there was given unto him a great sword.
B066C006V005	66	6	5	And when he had opened the third seal, I heard the third beast say, Come and see. And I beheld, and lo a black horse; and he that sat on him had a pair of balances in his hand.
B066C006V006	66	6	6	And I heard a voice in the midst of the four beasts say, A measure of wheat for a denarius, and three measures of barley for a denarius; and see you hurt not the oil and the wine.
B066C006V007	66	6	7	And when he had opened the fourth seal, I heard the voice of the fourth beast say, Come and see.
B066C006V008	66	6	8	And I looked, and behold a pale horse: and his name that sat on him was Death, and Hell followed with him. And power was given unto them over the fourth part of the earth, to kill with sword, and with hunger, and with death, and with the beasts of the earth.
B066C006V009	66	6	9	And when he had opened the fifth seal, I saw under the altar the souls of them that were slain for the word of God, and for the testimony which they held:
B066C006V010	66	6	10	And they cried with a loud voice, saying, How long, O Lord, holy and true, do you not judge and avenge our blood on them that dwell on the earth?
B066C006V011	66	6	11	And white robes were given unto every one of them; and it was said unto them, that they should rest yet for a little season, until their fellow servants also and their brothers, that should be killed as they were, should be fulfilled.
B066C006V012	66	6	12	And I beheld when he had opened the sixth seal, and, lo, there was a great earthquake; and the sun became black as sackcloth of hair, and the moon became as blood;
B066C006V013	66	6	13	And the stars of heaven fell unto the earth, just as a fig tree casts her untimely figs, when she is shaken of a mighty wind.
B066C006V014	66	6	14	And the heaven departed as a scroll when it is rolled together; and every mountain and island were moved out of their places.
B066C006V015	66	6	15	And the kings of the earth, and the great men, and the rich men, and the chief captains, and the mighty men, and every bondman, and every free man, hid themselves in the dens and in the rocks of the mountains;
B066C006V016	66	6	16	And said to the mountains and rocks, Fall on us, and hide us from the face of him that sits on the throne, and from the wrath of the Lamb:
B066C006V017	66	6	17	For the great day of his wrath is come; and who shall be able to stand?
B066C007V001	66	7	1	And after these things I saw four angels standing on the four corners of the earth, holding the four winds of the earth, that the wind should not blow on the earth, nor on the sea, nor on any tree.
B066C007V002	66	7	2	And I saw another angel ascending from the east, having the seal of the living God: and he cried with a loud voice to the four angels, to whom it was given to hurt the earth and the sea,
B066C007V003	66	7	3	Saying, Hurt not the earth, neither the sea, nor the trees, till we have sealed the servants of our God in their foreheads.
B066C007V004	66	7	4	And I heard the number of those who were sealed: and there were sealed a hundred and forty and four thousand of all the tribes of the children of Israel.
B066C007V005	66	7	5	Of the tribe of Juda were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Reuben were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Gad were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V006	66	7	6	Of the tribe of Aser were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Nephthalim were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Manasses were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V007	66	7	7	Of the tribe of Simeon were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Levi were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Issachar were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V008	66	7	8	Of the tribe of Zabulon were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Joseph were sealed twelve thousand. Of the tribe of Benjamin were sealed twelve thousand.
B066C007V009	66	7	9	After this I beheld, and, lo, a great multitude, which no man could number, of all nations, and kindreds, and people, and tongues, stood before the throne, and before the Lamb, clothed with white robes, and palms in their hands;
B066C007V010	66	7	10	And cried with a loud voice, saying, Salvation to our God which sits upon the throne, and unto the Lamb.
B066C007V011	66	7	11	And all the angels stood round about the throne, and about the elders and the four beasts, and fell before the throne on their faces, and worshipped God,
B066C007V012	66	7	12	Saying, Amen: Blessing, and glory, and wisdom, and thanksgiving, and honor, and power, and might, be unto our God forever and ever. Amen.
B066C007V013	66	7	13	And one of the elders answered, saying unto me, What are these which are arrayed in white robes? and from where came they?
B066C007V014	66	7	14	And I said unto him, Sir, you know. And he said to me, These are they which came out of great tribulation, and have washed their robes, and made them white in the blood of the Lamb.
B066C007V015	66	7	15	Therefore are they before the throne of God, and serve him day and night in his temple: and he that sits on the throne shall dwell among them.
B066C007V016	66	7	16	They shall hunger no more, neither thirst any more; neither shall the sun light on them, nor any heat.
B066C007V017	66	7	17	For the Lamb which is in the midst of the throne shall feed them, and shall lead them unto living fountains of waters: and God shall wipe away all tears from their eyes.
B066C008V001	66	8	1	And when he had opened the seventh seal, there was silence in heaven about the space of half an hour.
B066C008V002	66	8	2	And I saw the seven angels which stood before God; and to them were given seven trumpets.
B066C008V003	66	8	3	And another angel came and stood at the altar, having a golden censer; and there was given unto him much incense, that he should offer it with the prayers of all saints upon the golden altar which was before the throne.
B066C008V004	66	8	4	And the smoke of the incense, which came with the prayers of the saints, ascended up before God out of the angel's hand.
B066C008V005	66	8	5	And the angel took the censer, and filled it with fire of the altar, and cast it into the earth: and there were voices, and thunderings, and lightnings, and an earthquake.
B066C008V006	66	8	6	And the seven angels which had the seven trumpets prepared themselves to sound.
B066C008V007	66	8	7	The first angel sounded, and there followed hail and fire mingled with blood, and they were cast upon the earth: and the third part of trees was burnt up, and all green grass was burnt up.
B066C008V008	66	8	8	And the second angel sounded, and as it were a great mountain burning with fire was cast into the sea: and the third part of the sea became blood;
B066C008V009	66	8	9	And the third part of the creatures which were in the sea, and had life, died; and the third part of the ships were destroyed.
B066C008V010	66	8	10	And the third angel sounded, and there fell a great star from heaven, burning as it were a lamp, and it fell upon the third part of the rivers, and upon the fountains of waters;
B066C008V011	66	8	11	And the name of the star is called Wormwood: and the third part of the waters became wormwood; and many men died of the waters, because they were made bitter.
B066C008V012	66	8	12	And the fourth angel sounded, and the third part of the sun was smitten, and the third part of the moon, and the third part of the stars; so as the third part of them was darkened, and the day shone not for a third part of it, and the night likewise.
B066C008V013	66	8	13	And I beheld, and heard an angel flying through the midst of heaven, saying with a loud voice, Woe, woe, woe, to the inhabitants of the earth by reason of the other voices of the trumpet of the three angels, which are yet to sound!
B066C009V001	66	9	1	And the fifth angel sounded, and I saw a star fall from heaven unto the earth: and to him was given the key of the bottomless pit.
B066C009V002	66	9	2	And he opened the bottomless pit; and there arose a smoke out of the pit, as the smoke of a great furnace; and the sun and the air were darkened by reason of the smoke of the pit.
B066C009V003	66	9	3	And there came out of the smoke locusts upon the earth: and unto them was given power, as the scorpions of the earth have power.
B066C009V004	66	9	4	And it was commanded them that they should not hurt the grass of the earth, neither any green thing, neither any tree; but only those men which have not the seal of God in their foreheads.
B066C009V005	66	9	5	And to them it was given that they should not kill them, but that they should be tormented five months: and their torment was as the torment of a scorpion, when he strikes a man.
B066C009V006	66	9	6	And in those days shall men seek death, and shall not find it; and shall desire to die, and death shall flee from them.
B066C009V007	66	9	7	And the shapes of the locusts were like unto horses prepared unto battle; and on their heads were as it were crowns like gold, and their faces were as the faces of men.
B066C009V008	66	9	8	And they had hair as the hair of women, and their teeth were as the teeth of lions.
B066C009V009	66	9	9	And they had breastplates, as it were breastplates of iron; and the sound of their wings was as the sound of chariots of many horses running to battle.
B066C009V010	66	9	10	And they had tails like unto scorpions, and there were stings in their tails: and their power was to hurt men five months.
B066C009V011	66	9	11	And they had a king over them, which is the angel of the bottomless pit, whose name in the Hebrew tongue is Abaddon, but in the Greek tongue has his name Apollyon.
B066C009V012	66	9	12	One woe is past; and, behold, there come two woes more hereafter.
B066C009V013	66	9	13	And the sixth angel sounded, and I heard a voice from the four horns of the golden altar which is before God,
B066C009V014	66	9	14	Saying to the sixth angel which had the trumpet, Loose the four angels which are bound in the great river Euphrates.
B066C009V015	66	9	15	And the four angels were loosed, which were prepared for an hour, and a day, and a month, and a year, for to slay the third part of men.
B066C009V016	66	9	16	And the number of the army of the horsemen were two hundred thousand thousand: and I heard the number of them.
B066C009V017	66	9	17	And thus I saw the horses in the vision, and them that sat on them, having breastplates of fire, and of jacinth, and brimstone: and the heads of the horses were as the heads of lions; and out of their mouths issued fire and smoke and brimstone.
B066C009V018	66	9	18	By these three was the third part of men killed, by the fire, and by the smoke, and by the brimstone, which issued out of their mouths.
B066C009V019	66	9	19	For their power is in their mouth, and in their tails: for their tails were like unto serpents, and had heads, and with them they do hurt.
B066C009V020	66	9	20	And the rest of the men which were not killed by these plagues yet repented not of the works of their hands, that they should not worship devils, and idols of gold, and silver, and brass, and stone, and of wood: which neither can see, nor hear, nor walk:
B066C009V021	66	9	21	Neither repented they of their murders, nor of their sorceries, nor of their fornication, nor of their thefts.
B066C010V001	66	10	1	And I saw another mighty angel come down from heaven, clothed with a cloud: and a rainbow was upon his head, and his face was as it were the sun, and his feet as pillars of fire:
B066C010V002	66	10	2	And he had in his hand a little book open: and he set his right foot upon the sea, and his left foot on the earth,
B066C010V003	66	10	3	And cried with a loud voice, as when a lion roars: and when he had cried, seven thunders uttered their voices.
B066C010V004	66	10	4	And when the seven thunders had uttered their voices, I was about to write: and I heard a voice from heaven saying unto me, Seal up those things which the seven thunders uttered, and write them not.
B066C010V005	66	10	5	And the angel which I saw stand upon the sea and upon the earth lifted up his hand to heaven,
B066C010V006	66	10	6	And swore by him that lives for ever and ever, who created heaven, and the things that are in it, and the earth, and the things that are in it, and the sea, and the things which are in it, that there should be time no longer:
B066C010V007	66	10	7	But in the days of the voice of the seventh angel, when he shall begin to sound, the mystery of God should be finished, as he has declared to his servants the prophets.
B066C010V008	66	10	8	And the voice which I heard from heaven spoke unto me again, and said, Go and take the little book which is open in the hand of the angel which stands upon the sea and upon the earth.
B066C010V009	66	10	9	And I went unto the angel, and said unto him, Give me the little book. And he said unto me, Take it, and eat it up; and it shall make your belly bitter, but it shall be in your mouth sweet as honey.
B066C010V010	66	10	10	And I took the little book out of the angel's hand, and ate it up; and it was in my mouth sweet as honey: and as soon as I had eaten it, my belly was bitter.
B066C010V011	66	10	11	And he said unto me, You must prophesy again before many peoples, and nations, and tongues, and kings.
B066C011V001	66	11	1	And there was given me a reed like unto a rod: and the angel stood, saying, Rise, and measure the temple of God, and the altar, and them that worship in it.
B066C011V002	66	11	2	But the court which is outside the temple leave out, and measure it not; for it is given unto the Gentiles: and the holy city shall they tread under foot forty and two months.
B066C011V003	66	11	3	And I will give power unto my two witnesses, and they shall prophesy a thousand two hundred and threescore days, clothed in sackcloth.
B066C011V004	66	11	4	These are the two olive trees, and the two candlesticks standing before the God of the earth.
B066C011V005	66	11	5	And if any man will hurt them, fire proceeds out of their mouth, and devours their enemies: and if any man will hurt them, he must in this manner be killed.
B066C011V006	66	11	6	These have power to shut heaven, that it rain not in the days of their prophecy: and have power over waters to turn them to blood, and to smite the earth with all plagues, as often as they will.
B066C011V007	66	11	7	And when they shall have finished their testimony, the beast that ascends out of the bottomless pit shall make war against them, and shall overcome them, and kill them.
B066C011V008	66	11	8	And their dead bodies shall lie in the street of the great city, which spiritually is called Sodom and Egypt, where also our Lord was crucified.
B066C011V009	66	11	9	And they of the people and kindreds and tongues and nations shall see their dead bodies three days and a half, and shall not permit their dead bodies to be put in graves.
B066C011V010	66	11	10	And they that dwell upon the earth shall rejoice over them, and make merry, and shall send gifts one to another; because these two prophets tormented them that dwelled on the earth.
B066C011V011	66	11	11	And after three days and a half the spirit of life from God entered into them, and they stood upon their feet; and great fear fell upon those who saw them.
B066C011V012	66	11	12	And they heard a great voice from heaven saying unto them, Come up to here. And they ascended up to heaven in a cloud; and their enemies beheld them.
B066C011V013	66	11	13	And the same hour was there a great earthquake, and the tenth part of the city fell, and in the earthquake were slain of men seven thousand: and the remnant were frightened, and gave glory to the God of heaven.
B066C011V014	66	11	14	The second woe is past; and, behold, the third woe comes quickly.
B066C011V015	66	11	15	And the seventh angel sounded; and there were great voices in heaven, saying, The kingdoms of this world have become the kingdoms of our Lord, and of his Christ; and he shall reign forever and ever.
B066C011V016	66	11	16	And the four and twenty elders, which sat before God on their seats, fell upon their faces, and worshipped God,
B066C011V017	66	11	17	Saying, We give you thanks, O LORD God Almighty, which are, and was, and are to come; because you have taken to you your great power, and have reigned.
B066C011V018	66	11	18	And the nations were angry, and your wrath is come, and the time of the dead, that they should be judged, and that you should give reward unto your servants the prophets, and to the saints, and them that fear your name, small and great; and should destroy those who destroy the earth.
B066C011V019	66	11	19	And the temple of God was opened in heaven, and there was seen in his temple the ark of his testament: and there were lightnings, and voices, and thunderings, and an earthquake, and great hail.
B066C012V001	66	12	1	And there appeared a great wonder in heaven; a woman clothed with the sun, and the moon under her feet, and upon her head a crown of twelve stars:
B066C012V002	66	12	2	And she being with child cried, travailing in birth, and pained to be delivered.
B066C012V003	66	12	3	And there appeared another wonder in heaven; and behold a great red dragon, having seven heads and ten horns, and seven crowns upon his heads.
B066C012V004	66	12	4	And his tail drew the third part of the stars of heaven, and did cast them to the earth: and the dragon stood before the woman which was ready to be delivered, for to devour her child as soon as it was born.
B066C012V005	66	12	5	And she brought forth a man child, who was to rule all nations with a rod of iron: and her child was caught up unto God, and to his throne.
B066C012V006	66	12	6	And the woman fled into the wilderness, where she has a place prepared of God, that they should feed her there a thousand two hundred and threescore days.
B066C012V007	66	12	7	And there was war in heaven: Michael and his angels fought against the dragon; and the dragon fought and his angels,
B066C012V008	66	12	8	And prevailed not; neither was their place found any more in heaven.
B066C012V009	66	12	9	And the great dragon was cast out, that old serpent, called the Devil, and Satan, which deceives the whole world: he was cast out into the earth, and his angels were cast out with him.
B066C012V010	66	12	10	And I heard a loud voice saying in heaven, Now is come salvation, and strength, and the kingdom of our God, and the power of his Christ: for the accuser of our brothers is cast down, which accused them before our God day and night.
B066C012V011	66	12	11	And they overcame him by the blood of the Lamb, and by the word of their testimony; and they loved not their lives unto the death.
B066C012V012	66	12	12	Therefore rejoice, you heavens, and you that dwell in them. Woe to the inhabiters of the earth and of the sea! for the devil is come down unto you, having great wrath, because he knows that he has but a short time.
B066C012V013	66	12	13	And when the dragon saw that he was cast unto the earth, he persecuted the woman which brought forth the man child.
B066C012V014	66	12	14	And to the woman were given two wings of a great eagle, that she might fly into the wilderness, into her place, where she is nourished for a time, and times, and half a time, from the face of the serpent.
B066C012V015	66	12	15	And the serpent cast out of his mouth water as a flood after the woman, that he might cause her to be carried away of the flood.
B066C012V016	66	12	16	And the earth helped the woman, and the earth opened her mouth, and swallowed up the flood which the dragon cast out of his mouth.
B066C012V017	66	12	17	And the dragon was very angry with the woman, and went to make war with the remnant of her seed, which keep the commandments of God, and have the testimony of Jesus Christ.
B066C013V001	66	13	1	And I stood upon the sand of the sea, and saw a beast rise up out of the sea, having seven heads and ten horns, and upon his horns ten crowns, and upon his heads the name of blasphemy.
B066C013V002	66	13	2	And the beast which I saw was like unto a leopard, and his feet were as the feet of a bear, and his mouth as the mouth of a lion: and the dragon gave him his power, and his seat, and great authority.
B066C013V003	66	13	3	And I saw one of his heads as it were wounded to death; and his deadly wound was healed: and all the world wondered after the beast.
B066C013V004	66	13	4	And they worshipped the dragon which gave power unto the beast: and they worshipped the beast, saying, Who is like unto the beast? who is able to make war with him?
B066C013V005	66	13	5	And there was given unto him a mouth speaking great things and blasphemies; and power was given unto him to continue forty and two months.
B066C013V006	66	13	6	And he opened his mouth in blasphemy against God, to blaspheme his name, and his tabernacle, and them that dwell in heaven.
B066C013V007	66	13	7	And it was given unto him to make war with the saints, and to overcome them: and power was given him over all kindreds, and tongues, and nations.
B066C013V008	66	13	8	And all that dwell upon the earth shall worship him, whose names are not written in the book of life of the Lamb slain from the foundation of the world.
B066C013V009	66	13	9	If any man have an ear, let him hear.
B066C013V010	66	13	10	He that leads into captivity shall go into captivity: he that kills with the sword must be killed with the sword. Here is the patience and the faith of the saints.
B066C013V011	66	13	11	And I beheld another beast coming up out of the earth; and he had two horns like a lamb, and he spoke as a dragon.
B066C013V012	66	13	12	And he exercises all the power of the first beast before him, and causes the earth and those who dwell in it to worship the first beast, whose deadly wound was healed.
B066C013V013	66	13	13	And he does great wonders, so that he makes fire come down from heaven on the earth in the sight of men,
B066C013V014	66	13	14	And deceives them that dwell on the earth by the means of those miracles which he had power to do in the sight of the beast; saying to them that dwell on the earth, that they should make an image to the beast, which had the wound by a sword, and did live.
B066C013V015	66	13	15	And he had power to give life unto the image of the beast, that the image of the beast should both speak, and cause that as many as would not worship the image of the beast should be killed.
B066C013V016	66	13	16	And he causes all, both small and great, rich and poor, free and bond, to receive a mark in their right hand, or in their foreheads:
B066C013V017	66	13	17	And that no man might buy or sell, save he that had the mark, or the name of the beast, or the number of his name.
B066C013V018	66	13	18	Here is wisdom. Let him that has understanding count the number of the beast: for it is the number of a man; and his number is Six hundred threescore and six.
B066C014V001	66	14	1	And I looked, and, lo, a Lamb stood on the mount Zion, and with him a hundred forty and four thousand, having his Father's name written in their foreheads.
B066C014V002	66	14	2	And I heard a voice from heaven, as the voice of many waters, and as the voice of a great thunder: and I heard the voice of harpers harping with their harps:
B066C014V003	66	14	3	And they sung as it were a new song before the throne, and before the four beasts, and the elders: and no man could learn that song but the hundred and forty and four thousand, which were redeemed from the earth.
B066C014V004	66	14	4	These are they which were not defiled with women; for they are virgins. These are they which follow the Lamb wherever he goes. These were redeemed from among men, being the first fruits unto God and to the Lamb.
B066C014V005	66	14	5	And in their mouth was found no guile: for they are without fault before the throne of God.
B066C014V006	66	14	6	And I saw another angel fly in the midst of heaven, having the everlasting gospel to preach unto them that dwell on the earth, and to every nation, and kindred, and tongue, and people,
B066C014V007	66	14	7	Saying with a loud voice, Fear God, and give glory to him; for the hour of his judgment is come: and worship him that made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and the fountains of waters.
B066C014V008	66	14	8	And there followed another angel, saying, Babylon is fallen, is fallen, that great city, because she made all nations drink of the wine of the wrath of her fornication.
B066C014V009	66	14	9	And the third angel followed them, saying with a loud voice, If any man worship the beast and his image, and receive his mark in his forehead, or in his hand,
B066C014V010	66	14	10	The same shall drink of the wine of the wrath of God, which is poured out without mixture into the cup of his indignation; and he shall be tormented with fire and brimstone in the presence of the holy angels, and in the presence of the Lamb:
B066C014V011	66	14	11	And the smoke of their torment ascends up forever and ever: and they have no rest day nor night, who worship the beast and his image, and whosoever receives the mark of his name.
B066C014V012	66	14	12	Here is the patience of the saints: here are they that keep the commandments of God, and the faith of Jesus.
B066C014V013	66	14	13	And I heard a voice from heaven saying unto me, Write, Blessed are the dead which die in the Lord from now on: yes, says the Spirit, that they may rest from their labors; and their works do follow them.
B066C014V014	66	14	14	And I looked, and behold a white cloud, and upon the cloud one sat like unto the Son of man, having on his head a golden crown, and in his hand a sharp sickle.
B066C014V015	66	14	15	And another angel came out of the temple, crying with a loud voice to him that sat on the cloud, Thrust in your sickle, and reap: for the time is come for you to reap; for the harvest of the earth is ripe.
B066C014V016	66	14	16	And he that sat on the cloud thrust in his sickle on the earth; and the earth was reaped.
B066C014V017	66	14	17	And another angel came out of the temple which is in heaven, he also having a sharp sickle.
B066C014V018	66	14	18	And another angel came out from the altar, which had power over fire; and cried with a loud cry to him that had the sharp sickle, saying, Thrust in your sharp sickle, and gather the clusters of the vine of the earth; for her grapes are fully ripe.
B066C014V019	66	14	19	And the angel thrust in his sickle into the earth, and gathered the vine of the earth, and cast it into the great winepress of the wrath of God.
B066C014V020	66	14	20	And the winepress was trodden outside the city, and blood came out of the winepress, even unto the horse bridles, by the space of a thousand and six hundred furlongs.
B066C015V001	66	15	1	And I saw another sign in heaven, great and marvelous, seven angels having the seven last plagues; for in them is filled up the wrath of God.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	And I saw as it were a sea of glass mingled with fire: and them that had gotten the victory over the beast, and over his image, and over his mark, and over the number of his name, stand on the sea of glass, having the harps of God.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	And they sing the song of Moses the servant of God, and the song of the Lamb, saying, Great and marvelous are your works, Lord God Almighty; just and true are your ways, you King of saints.
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Who shall not fear you, O Lord, and glorify your name? for you only are holy: for all nations shall come and worship before you; for your judgments are made manifest.
B066C015V005	66	15	5	And after that I looked, and, behold, the temple of the tabernacle of the testimony in heaven was opened:
B066C015V006	66	15	6	And the seven angels came out of the temple, having the seven plagues, clothed in pure and white linen, and having their breasts girded with golden girdles.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	And one of the four beasts gave unto the seven angels seven golden vials full of the wrath of God, who lives forever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the temple was filled with smoke from the glory of God, and from his power; and no man was able to enter into the temple, till the seven plagues of the seven angels were fulfilled.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	And I heard a great voice out of the temple saying to the seven angels, 
B066C016V002	66	16	2	And the first went, and poured out his vial upon the earth; and there fell a noisome and grievous sore upon the men which had the mark of the beast, and upon those who worshipped his image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	And the second angel poured out his vial upon the sea; and it became as the blood of a dead man: and every living soul died in the sea.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	And the third angel poured out his vial upon the rivers and fountains of waters; and they became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	And I heard the angel of the waters say, You are righteous, O Lord, which are, and was, and shall be, because you have judged thus.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	For they have shed the blood of saints and prophets, and you have given them blood to drink; for they are worthy.
B066C016V007	66	16	7	And I heard another out of the altar say, Even so, Lord God Almighty, true and righteous are your judgments.
B066C016V008	66	16	8	And the fourth angel poured out his vial upon the sun; and power was given unto him to scorch men with fire.
B066C016V009	66	16	9	And men were scorched with great heat, and blasphemed the name of God, which has power over these plagues: and they repented not to give him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	And the fifth angel poured out his vial upon the seat of the beast; and his kingdom was full of darkness; and they gnawed their tongues for pain,
B066C016V011	66	16	11	And blasphemed the God of heaven because of their pains and their sores, and repented not of their deeds.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	And the sixth angel poured out his vial upon the great river Euphrates; and the water of it was dried up, that the way of the kings of the east might be prepared.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	And I saw three unclean spirits like frogs come out of the mouth of the dragon, and out of the mouth of the beast, and out of the mouth of the false prophet.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	For they are the spirits of devils, working miracles, which go forth unto the kings of the earth and of the whole world, to gather them to the battle of that great day of God Almighty.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	
        
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And he gathered them together into a place called in the Hebrew tongue Armageddon.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	And the seventh angel poured out his vial into the air; and there came a great voice out of the temple of heaven, from the throne, saying, 
