B066C016V019	66	16	19	And the great city was divided into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell: and great Babylon came in remembrance before God, to give unto her the cup of the wine of the fierceness of his wrath.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	And every island fled away, and the mountains were not found.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And there fell upon men a great hail out of heaven, every stone about the weight of a talent: and men blasphemed God because of the plague of the hail; for the plague of it was exceedingly great.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	And there came one of the seven angels which had the seven vials, and talked with me, saying unto me, Come to here; I will show unto you the judgment of the great whore that sits upon many waters:
B066C017V002	66	17	2	With whom the kings of the earth have committed fornication, and the inhabitants of the earth have been made drunk with the wine of her fornication.
B066C017V003	66	17	3	So he carried me away in the spirit into the wilderness: and I saw a woman sit upon a scarlet colored beast, full of names of blasphemy, having seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	And the woman was arrayed in purple and scarlet color, and decked with gold and precious stones and pearls, having a golden cup in her hand full of abominations and filthiness of her fornication:
B066C017V005	66	17	5	And upon her forehead was a name written, MYSTERY, BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS AND ABOMINATIONS OF THE EARTH.
B066C017V006	66	17	6	And I saw the woman drunken with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Jesus: and when I saw her, I wondered with great admiration.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	And the angel said unto me, Why did you marvel? I will tell you the mystery of the woman, and of the beast that carries her, which has the seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast that you saw was, and is not; and shall ascend out of the bottomless pit, and go into perdition: and they that dwell on the earth shall wonder, whose names were not written in the book of life from the foundation of the world, when they behold the beast that was, and is not, and yet is.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	And here is the mind which has wisdom. The seven heads are seven mountains, on which the woman sits.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	And there are seven kings: five are fallen, and one is, and the other is not yet come; and when he comes, he must continue a short space.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the beast that was, and is not, even he is the eighth, and is of the seven, and goes into perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	And the ten horns which you saw are ten kings, which have received no kingdom as yet; but receive power as kings one hour with the beast.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	These have one mind, and shall give their power and strength unto the beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	These shall make war with the Lamb, and the Lamb shall overcome them: for he is Lord of lords, and King of kings: and they that are with him are called, and chosen, and faithful.
B066C017V015	66	17	15	And he says unto me, The waters which you saw, where the whore sits, are peoples, and multitudes, and nations, and tongues.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns which you saw upon the beast, these shall hate the whore, and shall make her desolate and naked, and shall eat her flesh, and burn her with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put in their hearts to fulfill his will, and to agree, and give their kingdom unto the beast, until the words of God shall be fulfilled.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	And the woman which you saw is that great city, which reigns over the kings of the earth.
B066C018V001	66	18	1	And after these things I saw another angel come down from heaven, having great power; and the earth was lightened with his glory.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	And he cried mightily with a strong voice, saying, Babylon the great is fallen, is fallen, and is become the habitation of devils, and the hold of every foul spirit, and a cage of every unclean and hateful bird.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her fornication, and the kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, and the merchants of the earth are waxed rich through the abundance of her delicacies.
B066C018V004	66	18	4	And I heard another voice from heaven, saying, Come out of her, my people, that you be not partakers of her sins, and that you receive not of her plagues.
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins have reached unto heaven, and God has remembered her iniquities.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Reward her just as she rewarded you, and double unto her double according to her works: in the cup which she has filled fill to her double.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	How much she has glorified herself, and lived deliciously, so much torment and sorrow give her: for she says in her heart, I sit a queen, and am no widow, and shall see no sorrow.
B066C018V008	66	18	8	Therefore shall her plagues come in one day, death, and mourning, and famine; and she shall be utterly burned with fire: for strong is the Lord God who judges her.
B066C018V009	66	18	9	And the kings of the earth, who have committed fornication and lived deliciously with her, shall bewail her, and lament for her, when they shall see the smoke of her burning,
B066C018V010	66	18	10	Standing afar off for the fear of her torment, saying, Alas, alas that great city Babylon, that mighty city! for in one hour is your judgment come.
B066C018V011	66	18	11	And the merchants of the earth shall weep and mourn over her; for no man buys their merchandise any more:
B066C018V012	66	18	12	The merchandise of gold, and silver, and precious stones, and of pearls, and fine linen, and purple, and silk, and scarlet, and all citron wood, and all manner vessels of ivory, and all manner vessels of most precious wood, and of brass, and iron, and marble,
B066C018V013	66	18	13	And cinnamon, and odors, and ointments, and frankincense, and wine, and oil, and fine flour, and wheat, and beasts, and sheep, and horses, and chariots, and slaves, and souls of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	And the fruits that your soul lusted after are departed from you, and all things which were dainty and good are departed from you, and you shall find them no more at all.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	The merchants of these things, which were made rich by her, shall stand afar off for the fear of her torment, weeping and wailing,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	And saying, Alas, alas that great city, that was clothed in fine linen, and purple, and scarlet, and decked with gold, and precious stones, and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	For in one hour so great riches is come to nothing. And every shipmaster, and all the company in ships, and sailors, and as many as trade by sea, stood afar off,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	And cried when they saw the smoke of her burning, saying, What city is like unto this great city!
B066C018V019	66	18	19	And they cast dust on their heads, and cried, weeping and wailing, saying, Alas, alas that great city, in which were made rich all that had ships in the sea by reason of her costliness! for in one hour is she made desolate.
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Rejoice over her, you heaven, and you holy apostles and prophets; for God has avenged you on her.
B066C018V021	66	18	21	And a mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone, and cast it into the sea, saying, Thus with violence shall that great city Babylon be thrown down, and shall be found no more at all.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	And the voice of harpers, and musicians, and of pipers, and trumpeters, shall be heard no more at all in you; and no craftsman, of whatsoever craft he be, shall be found any more in you; and the sound of a millstone shall be heard no more at all in you;
B066C018V023	66	18	23	And the light of a candle shall shine no more at all in you; and the voice of the bridegroom and of the bride shall be heard no more at all in you: for your merchants were the great men of the earth; for by your sorceries were all nations deceived.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in her was found the blood of prophets, and of saints, and of all that were slain upon the earth.
B066C019V001	66	19	1	And after these things I heard a great voice of many people in heaven, saying, Alleluia; Salvation, and glory, and honor, and power, unto the Lord our God:
B066C019V002	66	19	2	For true and righteous are his judgments: for he has judged the great whore, which did corrupt the earth with her fornication, and has avenged the blood of his servants at her hand.
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And again they said, Alleluia And her smoke rose up forever and ever.
B066C019V004	66	19	4	And the four and twenty elders and the four beasts fell down and worshipped God that sat on the throne, saying, Amen; Alleluia.
B066C019V005	66	19	5	And a voice came out of the throne, saying, Praise our God, all you his servants, and you that fear him, both small and great.
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I heard as it were the voice of a great multitude, and as the voice of many waters, and as the voice of mighty thunderings, saying, Alleluia: for the Lord God omnipotent reigns.
