B066C021V007	66	21	7	
        
B066C021V008	66	21	8	
        
B066C021V009	66	21	9	And there came unto me one of the seven angels which had the seven vials full of the seven last plagues, and talked with me, saying, Come to here, I will show you the bride, the Lamb's wife.
B066C021V010	66	21	10	And he carried me away in the spirit to a great and high mountain, and showed me that great city, the holy Jerusalem, descending out of heaven from God,
B066C021V011	66	21	11	Having the glory of God: and her light was like unto a stone most precious, even like a jasper stone, clear as crystal;
B066C021V012	66	21	12	And had a wall great and high, and had twelve gates, and at the gates twelve angels, and names written thereon, which are the names of the twelve tribes of the children of Israel:
B066C021V013	66	21	13	On the east three gates; on the north three gates; on the south three gates; and on the west three gates.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	And the wall of the city had twelve foundations, and in them the names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	And he that talked with me had a golden reed to measure the city, and the gates of it, and the wall of it.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	And the city lies foursquare, and the length is as large as the breadth: and he measured the city with the reed, twelve thousand furlongs. The length and the breadth and the height of it are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And he measured the wall of it, a hundred and forty and four cubits, according to the measure of a man, that is, of the angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	And the building of the wall of it was of jasper: and the city was pure gold, like unto clear glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	And the foundations of the wall of the city were garnished with all manner of precious stones. The first foundation was jasper; the second, sapphire; the third, a chalcedony; the fourth, an emerald;
B066C021V020	66	21	20	The fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, sardius; the seventh, chrysolyte; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, a topaz; the tenth, a chrysoprasus; the eleventh, a jacinth; the twelfth, an amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	And the twelve gates were twelve pearls: every several gate was of one pearl: and the street of the city was pure gold, as it were transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	And I saw no temple in it: for the Lord God Almighty and the Lamb are the temple of it.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	And the city had no need of the sun, neither of the moon, to shine in it: for the glory of God did lighten it, and the Lamb is the light of it.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	And the nations of those who are saved shall walk in the light of it: and the kings of the earth do bring their glory and honor into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And the gates of it shall not be shut at all by day: for there shall be no night there.
B066C021V026	66	21	26	And they shall bring the glory and honor of the nations into it.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	And there shall in no way enter into it any thing that defiles, neither whatsoever works abomination, or makes a lie: but they which are written in the Lamb's book of life.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	And he showed me a pure river of water of life, clear as crystal, proceeding out of the throne of God and of the Lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	In the midst of the street of it, and on either side of the river, was there the tree of life, which bore twelve manner of fruits, and yielded her fruit every month: and the leaves of the tree were for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	And there shall be no more curse: but the throne of God and of the Lamb shall be in it; and his servants shall serve him:
B066C022V004	66	22	4	And they shall see his face; and his name shall be on their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And there shall be no night there; and they need no candle, neither light of the sun; for the Lord God gives them light: and they shall reign forever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	And he said unto me, These sayings are faithful and true: and the Lord God of the holy prophets sent his angel to show unto his servants the things which must shortly be done.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	
        
B066C022V008	66	22	8	And I John saw these things, and heard them. And when I had heard and seen, I fell down to worship before the feet of the angel which showed me these things.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	Then says he unto me, See you do it not: for I am your fellow servant, and of your brothers the prophets, and of those who keep the sayings of this book: worship God.
B066C022V010	66	22	10	And he says unto me, Seal not the sayings of the prophecy of this book: for the time is at hand.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	He that is unjust, let him be unjust still: and he which is filthy, let him be filthy still: and he that is righteous, let him be righteous still: and he that is holy, let him be holy still.
B066C022V012	66	22	12	
        
B066C022V013	66	22	13	
        
B066C022V014	66	22	14	Blessed are they that do his commandments, that they may have right to the tree of life, and may enter in through the gates into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	For outside are dogs, and sorcerers, and whoremongers, and murderers, and idolaters, and whosoever loves and makes a lie.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	
        
B066C022V017	66	22	17	And the Spirit and the bride say, Come. And let him that hears say, Come. And let him that is athirst come. And whosoever will, let him take the water of life freely.
B066C022V018	66	22	18	For I testify unto every man that hears the words of the prophecy of this book, If any man shall add unto these things, God shall add unto him the plagues that are written in this book:
B066C022V019	66	22	19	And if any man shall take away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God shall take away his part out of the book of life, and out of the holy city, and from the things which are written in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	He which testifies these things says, 
B066C022V021	66	22	21	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.
